{"title_page": "Ayam goreng kalasan", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|Javanese fried chicken}}\n{{Infobox Prepared Food\n| name             = Ayam Goreng Kalasan\n| image            = Ayam goreng kalasan.JPG\n| caption          = \n| alternate_name   = \n| country          = [[Indonesia]]\n| region           = Sleman, [[Yogyakarta]]\n| creator          = \n| course           = \n| served           = \n| main_ingredient  = \n| variations       = \n| calories         =  \n| other            = \n}}\n\n'''Ayam Goreng Kalasan''' ({{lang-jv|\ua9b2\ua9aa\ua9a9\ua9c0\u200b\ua992\ua9ba\ua9b4\ua9ab\ua9ba\ua981\u200b\ua98f\ua9ad\ua9b1\ua9a4\ua9c0|Ayam Gor\u00e8ng Kalasan}}) is one type of processed fried chicken that is typical from the area of \u200b\u200bKalasan, Sleman, Yogyakarta.  The specialty of Kalasan Fried Chicken is the taste of the chicken which is savory and kramesan which is very distinctive.  Because of its distinctive taste, Kalasan Fried Chicken has become one of the culinary that is very liked by the community and tourists visiting Yogyakarta.\n\nThe special taste of the Kalasan Fried Chicken cannot be separated from the intervention of Mbok Berek, a person who first introduced this fried chicken.  According to several sources, Mbok Berek first introduced him through his small food stall in the area of \u200b\u200bTirtomartani Village, Kalasan District, precisely on the side of the Jogja - Solo road.  Because the taste is unique and different from other fried chicken at that time, Mbok Berek fried chicken is very popular with the people there.\n\nThe specialty of Kalasan Fried Chicken is its crispy, crispy kremes.  The crispy taste of kramesan is made from starch flour dough, so that it produces crispy crispy and not hard.  For chickens used are usually native chicken seasoned with salt and onions.  Although the seasoning used is fairly simple, it can produce a savory flavor that fits right on this fried chicken. In addition, the chicken is cooked in a special way so as to produce tender meat and has perfect maturity.<ref name=\"JP-7rice\">{{Cite news|url= https://m.detik.com/food/berita-boga/d-1224068/ayam-goreng-kalasan-legit-gurih-sedap |title= traditional Indonesian fried chicken dishes (Indonesian)|website=Detik.com|language=Id|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nAyam goreng kalasan is usually served with vegetables such as cucumbers, basil leaves, and sliced \u200b\u200bcabbage.  In addition, special chili sauce is made to accompany this fried chicken.  For one serving of fried chicken contains one fried chicken without claws and viscera. Ayam goreng kalasan is very suitable to be served while warm with warm rice too. For cremation, usually served separately, so we are free to use it according to taste.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Food|Indonesia}}\n* [[Ayam goreng]]\n* [[Ayam penyet]]\n* [[Javanese cuisine]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Indonesian cuisine}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|Javanese fried chicken}}\n{{Infobox Prepared Food\n| name             = Ayam Goreng Kalasan\n| image            = Ayam goreng kalasan.JPG\n| caption          = \n| alternate_name   = \n| country          = [[Indonesia]]\n| region           = Sleman, [[Yogyakarta]]\n| creator          = \n| course           = \n| served           = \n| main_ingredient  = \n| variations       = \n| calories         =  \n| other            = \n}}\n\n'''Ayam Goreng Kalasan''' ({{lang-jv|\ua9b2\ua9aa\ua9a9\ua9c0\u200b\ua992\ua9ba\ua9b4\ua9ab\ua9ba\ua981\u200b\ua98f\ua9ad\ua9b1\ua9a4\ua9c0|Ayam Gor\u00e8ng Kalasan}}) is one type of processed fried chicken that is typical from the area of \u200b\u200bKalasan, Sleman, Yogyakarta.  The specialty of Kalasan Fried Chicken is the taste of the chicken which is savory and kramesan which is very distinctive.  Because of its distinctive taste, Kalasan Fried Chicken has become one of the culinary that is very liked by the community and tourists visiting Yogyakarta.\n\nThe special taste of the Kalasan Fried Chicken cannot be separated from the intervention of Mbok Berek, a person who first introduced this fried chicken.  According to several sources, Mbok Berek first introduced him through his small food stall in the area of \u200b\u200bTirtomartani Village, Kalasan District, precisely on the side of the Jogja - Solo road.  Because the taste is unique and different from other fried chicken at that time, Mbok Berek fried chicken is very popular with the people there.\n\nThe specialty of Kalasan Fried Chicken is its crispy, crispy kremes.  The crispy taste of kramesan is made from starch flour dough, so that it produces crispy crispy and not hard.  For chickens used are usually native chicken seasoned with salt and onions.  Although the seasoning used is fairly simple, it can produce a savory flavor that fits right on this fried chicken. In addition, the chicken is cooked in a special way so as to produce tender meat and has perfect maturity.<ref name=\"JP-7rice\">{{Cite news|url= https://m.detik.com/food/berita-boga/d-1224068/ayam-goreng-kalasan-legit-gurih-sedap |title= traditional Indonesian fried chicken dishes (Indonesian)|website=Detik.com|language=Id|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nAyam goreng kalasan is usually served with vegetables such as cucumbers, basil leaves, and sliced \u200b\u200bcabbage.  In addition, special chili sauce is made to accompany this fried chicken.  For one serving of fried chicken contains one fried chicken without claws and viscera. Ayam goreng kalasan is very suitable to be served while warm with warm rice too. For cremation, usually served separately, so we are free to use it according to taste.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Food|Indonesia}}\n* [[Ayam goreng]]\n* [[Ayam penyet]]\n* [[Javanese cuisine]]\n\n==Reference==\n\n{{Indonesian cuisine}}\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reflist", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ayam_goreng_kalasan"}
{"title_page": "List of Dua Lipa concert tours", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\nThis is a list of the '''concert tours''' undertaken by English singer [[Dua Lipa]].\n\n==2016 UK Tour (2016)==\n{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name=2016 UK Tour\n|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]\n|type=Concert tour\n|image=File:Dua_Lipa_2016_UK_Tour.jpg\n|image_size=120\n|border=yes\n|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''\n|start_date={{Start date|2016|01|16|df=yes}}\n|end_date={{End date|2016|02|02|df=yes}}\n|number_of_legs=1\n|number_of_shows=7\n|last_tour=\n|next_tour=Hotter Than Hell Tour<br />(2016)\n|this_tour='''2016 UK Tour'''<br />(2016)\n}}\n\nDuring early 2016, Dua Lipa toured the UK.\n\n===Tour dates===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-announces-debut-uk-tour|title=Dua Lipa announces debut UK tour|work=The Line of Best Fit|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.musomuso.co.uk/news/london-based-songwriter-dua-lipa-announces-2016-uk-tour|title=London based songwriter DUA LIPA announces 2016 UK tour....|work=musomuso.com|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|16 January 2016\n|[[Bristol]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[England]]\n|Louisiana\n|-\n|17 January 2016\n|[[Brighton]]\n|The Hope\n|-\n|26 January 2016\n|[[Glasgow]]\n|[[Scotland]]\n|[[O2 ABC Glasgow|O2 ABC]]\n|-\n|27 January 2016\n|[[Manchester]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" |England\n|Soup Kitchen\n|-\n|29 January 2016\n|[[Birmingham]]\n|Sunflower Lounge\n|-\n|30 January 2016\n|[[Nottingham]]\n|Stealth\n|-\n|2 February 2016\n|[[London]]\n|[[Oslo (Hackney)|Oslo Hackney]]\n|}\n\n==Hotter Than Hell Tour (2016)==\n{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name=Hotter Than Hell Tour\n|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]\n|type=Concert tour\n|image=File:Hotter_Than_Hell.png\n|image_size=120\n|border=yes\n|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''\n|start_date={{Start date|2016|10|05|df=yes}}\n|end_date={{End date|2016|12|09|df=yes}}\n|number_of_legs=1\n|number_of_shows=11\n|last_tour=2016 UK Tour<br />(2016)\n|next_tour=US and Europe Tour<br />(2017)\n|this_tour='''Hotter Than Hell Tour'''<br />(2016)\n}}\n\nThe '''Hotter Than Hell Tour''' is the first official headlining concert tour by Dua Lipa. It began in Dublin, Ireland on 5 October 2016, and ended on 2 December 2016, in Birmingham, E.\n\n===Background===\nOn 10 May 2016, Lipa announced the first 11 European tour dates and said \"more dates were to be announced\". Pre-sale for the announced dates began on 11 May 2016 and general sale began on 13 May 2016. More dates were announced gradually within the next few months. The Birmingham date was originally scheduled for 9 October, but was later rescheduled to 2 December.\n\n===Set list===\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=Setlist|content=# [[Last Dance (Dua Lipa song)|Last Dance]]\n# \"Dreams\"\n# \"Bad Together\"\n# \"Room For 2\"\n# \"[[Blow Your Mind (Mwah)]]\"\n# \"Want To\"\n# \"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n# \"New Love\"\n# \"Running\"\n# \"Genesis\"\n# \"[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be The One]]\"\n# \"For Julian\"\n# \"[[Hotter than Hell (Dua Lipa song)|Hotter Than Hell]]\"\n}}\n\n===Opening act===\n* Hare Squead\n\n===Tour dates===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dualipa.com/hotter-hell-tour/dua-lipa_eu_insta/|title=Dua Lipa_EU_insta - Dua Lipa|work=Dua Lipa|access-date=2018-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028190306/https://dualipa.com/hotter-hell-tour/dua-lipa_eu_insta/|archive-date=28 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|5 October 2016\n|[[Dublin]]\n|[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n|{{sort|Academy, The|[[The Academy (music venue)|The Academy]]}}\n|-\n|7 October 2016\n|Manchester\n| rowspan=\"2\" |England\n|Gorilla\n|-\n|10 October 2016\n|London\n|[[KOKO (music venue)|KOKO]]\n|-\n|14 October 2016\n|[[Brussels]]\n|[[Belgium]]\n|[[Ancienne Belgique]]\n|-\n|17 October 2016\n|[[Copenhagen]]\n|[[Denmark]]\n|Vega\n|-\n|19 October 2016\n|[[Berlin]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Germany]]\n|Heimathafen Neukolln\n|-\n|20 October 2016\n|[[Hamburg]]\n|[[Mojo Club]]\n|-\n|22 October 2016\n|[[Cologne]]\n|Kantine\n|-\n|24 October 2016\n|[[Frankfurt]]\n|Gibson\n|-\n|25 October 2016\n|[[Munich]]\n|Backstage Werk\n|-\n|27 October 2016\n|[[Milan]]\n|[[Italy]]\n|Tunnel\n|-\n|2 December 2016{{efn|The concert of 2 December 2016 in Birmingham was originally scheduled for 9 October 2016}}\n|Birmingham\n|England\n|[[Digbeth Institute|O2 Institute2]]\n|}\n\n==US and Europe Tour (2017)==\n{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name=US and Europe Tour\n|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]\n|type=Concert tour\n|image=File:Us_and_Europe_Tour.jpg\n|image_size=120\n|border=yes\n|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''\n|start_date={{Start date|2017|02|24|df=yes}}\n|end_date={{End date|2017|04|13|df=yes}}\n|number_of_legs=2\n|number_of_shows=15 in North America<br>6 in Europe <br>21 total\n|last_tour=[[Hotter Than Hell Tour]]<br />(2016)\n|next_tour=The Self-Titled Tour<br />(2017-18)\n|this_tour='''US and Europe Tour'''<br />(2017)\n}}\n\nThe '''US and Europe Tour''' is the second official headlining concert tour by Dua Lipa. It is in support of her self-titled debut album ''Dua Lipa.'' The tour began on 24 February 2017 in Chicago, Illinois, and is scheduled to conclude on 13 April 2017 in London, United Kingdom.\n\n===Background===\nDuring January 2017, Dua started to tease an exciting announcement on social media and on 17 January she revealed the North American tour with 15 confirmed dates. Tickets for all North American dates went on sale on 21 January. On 20 January 2017, Dua announced a small batch of European dates as part of the 2017 concert tour. Tickets for European dates went on sale on 3 February.\n\n===Set list===\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=Setlist|content=# Last Dance\n# \"Want To\"\n# \"Bad Together\"\n# \"Room For 2\"\n# \"Hotter Than Hell\"\n# \"Dreams\"\n# \"[[No Lie (Sean Paul song)|No Lie]]\"\n# \"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n# \"[[Scared to be Lonely]]\"\n# \"Genesis\"\n# \"Be The One\"\n# \"Blow Your Mind (Mwah)\"\n}}\n\n===Opening acts===\n* [[Ro Ransom]] (North America)\n* Off Bloom (Europe)\n\n===Tour dates===\n\n==== North American leg (24 February \u2013 17 March 2017) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/dualipa/status/821371743562514433|title=DUA LIPA on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|24 February 2017\n|[[Chicago]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[United States]]\n|Lincoln Hall\n|-\n|25 February 2017\n|[[Detroit]]\n|{{sort|Shelter, The|The Shelter}}\n|-\n|27 February 2017\n|[[Toronto]]\n|[[Canada]]\n|[[Mod Club Theatre]]\n|-\n|1 March 2017\n|[[New York City]]\n| rowspan=\"12\" |United States\n|[[Irving Plaza]]\n|-\n|2 March 2017\n|[[Philadelphia]]\n|{{sort|Founrdy, The|[[The Fillmore|The Foundry]]}}\n|-\n|4 March 2017\n|[[Boston]]\n|[[Paradise Rock Club]]\n|-\n|5 March 2017\n|[[Washington, D.C.]]\n|Rock & Roll Hotel\n|-\n|7 March 2017\n|[[Atlanta]]\n|The 