y\n|Backstage Werk\n|-\n|20 October 2017\n|[[Frankfurt]]\n|[[Batschkapp]]\n|-\n|21 October 2017\n|[[Esch-sur-Alzette]]\n|[[Luxembourg]]\n|[[Rockhal]]\n|-\n|24 October 2017\n|[[Cologne]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Germany\n|[[Live Music Hall]]\n|-\n|25 October 2017\n|[[Berlin]]\n|Astra \n|-\n|27 October 2017\n|[[Hamburg]]\n|[[Docks (nightclub)|Docks]]\n|-\n|29 October 2017\n|[[Oslo]]\n|[[Norway]]\n|[[Rockefeller Music Hall]]\n|-\n|1 November 2017\n|[[Copenhagen]]\n|Denmark\n|Amager Bio\n|-\n|3 November 2017\n|[[Antwerp]]\n|[[Belgium]]\n|[[Lotto Arena]]\n|-\n|5 November 2017\n|[[Amsterdam]]\n|Netherlands\n|[[AFAS Live]]\n|-\n|6 November 2017\n|[[London]]\n|England\n|[[O2 Brixton Academy|O2 Academy Brixton]]\n|}\n\n==== South American leg (9\u201313 November 2017) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|9 November 2017\n|[[S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n|[[Brazil]]\n|Audio Club\n|-\n|13 November 2017\n|[[Buenos Aires]]\n|[[Argentina]]\n|Vorterix Theatre\n|}\n\n==== North American leg (19 November 2017 \u2013 17 February 2018) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7964661/dua-lipa-north-american-tour-dates|title=Dua Lipa Announces North American Tour dates|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|19 November 2017{{efn|The concert of 19 November 2017 in Mexico City is part of [[Corona Capital]] festival.}}\n|[[Mexico City]]\n|[[Mexico]]\n|[[Aut\u00f3dromo Hermanos 