e sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-announces-debut-uk-tour|title=Dua Lipa announces debut UK tour|work=The Line of Best Fit|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.musomuso.co.uk/news/london-based-songwriter-dua-lipa-announces-2016-uk-tour|title=London based songwriter DUA LIPA announces 2016 UK tour....|work=musomuso.com|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|16 January 2016\n|[[Bristol]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[England]]\n|Louisiana\n|-\n|17 January 2016\n|[[Brighton]]\n|The Hope\n|-\n|26 January 2016\n|[[Glasgow]]\n|[[Scotland]]\n|[[O2 ABC Glasgow|O2 ABC]]\n|-\n|27 January 2016\n|[[Manchester]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" |England\n|Soup Kitchen\n|-\n|29 January 2016\n|[[Birmingham]]\n|Sunflower Lounge\n|-\n|30 January 2016\n|[[Nottingham]]\n|Stealth\n|-\n|2 February 2016\n|[[London]]\n|[[Oslo (Hackney)|Oslo Hackney]]\n|}\n\n==Hotter Than Hell Tour (2016)==\n{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name=Hotter Than Hell Tour\n|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]\n|type=Concert tour\n|image=File:Hotter_Than_Hell.png\n|image_size=120\n|border=yes\n|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''\n|start_date={{Start date|2016|10|05|df=yes}}\n|end_date={{End date|2016|12|09|df=yes}}\n|number_of_legs=1\n|number_of_shows=11\n|last_tour=2016 UK Tour<br />(2016)\n|next_tour=US and Europe Tour<br />(2017)\n|this_tour='''Hotter Than Hell Tour'''<br />(2016)\n}}\n\nThe '''Hotter Than Hell Tour''' is the first official headlining concert tour by Dua Lipa. It began in Dublin, Ireland on 5 October 2016, and ended on 2 December 2016, in Birmingham, E.\n\n===Background===\nOn 10 May 2016, Lipa announced the first 11 European tour dates and said \"more dates were to be announced\". Pre-sale for the announced dates began on 11 May 2016 and general sale began on 13 May 2016. More dates were announced gradually within the next few months. The Birmingham date was originally scheduled for 9 October, but was later rescheduled to 2 December.\n\n===Set list===\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=Setlist|content=# [[Last Dance (Dua Lipa song)|Last Dance]]\n# \"Dreams\"\n# \"Bad Together\"\n# \"Room For 2\"\n# \"[[Blow Your Mind (Mwah)]]\"\n# \"Want To\"\n# \"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n# \"New Love\"\n# \"Running\"\n# \"Genesis\"\n# \"[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be The One]]\"\n# \"For Julian\"\n# \"[[Hotter than Hell (Dua Lipa song)|Hotter Than Hell]]\"\n}}\n\n===Opening act===\n* Hare Squead\n\n===Tour dates===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dualipa.com/hotter-hell-tour/dua-lipa_eu_insta/|title=Dua Lipa_EU_insta - Dua Lipa|work=Dua Lipa|access-date=2018-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028190306/https://dualipa.com/hotter-hell-tour/dua-lipa_eu_insta/|archive-date=28 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|5 October 2016\n|[[Dublin]]\n|[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n|{{sort|Academy, The|[[The Academy (music venue)|The Academy]]}}\n|-\n|7 October 2016\n|Manchester\n| rowspan=\"2\" |England\n|Gorilla\n|-\n|10 October 2016\n|London\n|[[KOKO (music venue)|KOKO]]\n|-\n|14 October 2016\n|[[Brussels]]\n|[[Belgium]]\n|[[Ancienne Belgique]]\n|-\n|17 October 2016\n|[[Copenhagen]]\n|[[Denmark]]\n|Vega\n|-\n|19 October 2016\n|[[Berlin]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Germany]]\n|Heimathafen Neukolln\n|-\n|20 October 2016\n|[[Hamburg]]\n|[[Mojo Club]]\n|-\n|22 October 2016\n|[[Cologne]]\n|Kantine\n|-\n|24 October 2016\n|[[Frankfurt]]\n|Gibson\n|-\n|25 October 2016\n|[[Munich]]\n|Backstage Werk\n|-\n|27 October 2016\n|[[Milan]]\n|[[Italy]]\n|Tunnel\n|-\n|2 December 2016{{efn|The concert of 2 December 2016 in Birmingham was originally scheduled for 9 October 2016}}\n|Birmingham\n|England\n|[[Digbeth Institute|O2 Institute2]]\n|}\n\n==US and Europe Tour (2017)==\n{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name=US and Europe Tour\n|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]\n|type=Concert tour\n|image=File:Us_and_Europe_Tour.jpg\n|image_size=120\n|border=yes\n|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''\n|start_date={{Start date|2017|02|24|df=yes}}\n|end_date={{End date|2017|04|13|df=yes}}\n|number_of_legs=2\n|number_of_shows=15 in North America<br>6 in Europe <br>21 total\n|last_tour=[[Hotter Than Hell Tour]]<br />(2016)\n|next_tour=The Self-Titled Tour<br />(2017-18)\n|this_tour='''US and Europe Tour'''<br />(2017)\n}}\n\nThe '''US and Europe Tour''' is the second official headlining concert tour by Dua Lipa. It is in support of her self-titled debut album ''Dua Lipa.'' The tour began on 24 February 2017 in Chicago, Illinois, and is scheduled to conclude on 13 April 2017 in London, United Kingdom.\n\n===Background===\nDuring January 2017, Dua started to tease an exciting announcement on social media and on 17 January she revealed the North American tour with 15 confirmed dates. Tickets for all North American dates went on sale on 21 January. On 20 January 2017, Dua announced a small batch of European dates as part of the 2017 concert tour. Tickets for European dates went on sale on 3 February.\n\n===Set list===\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=Setlist|content=# Last Dance\n# \"Want To\"\n# \"Bad Together\"\n# \"Room For 2\"\n# \"Hotter Than Hell\"\n# \"Dreams\"\n# \"[[No Lie (Sean Paul song)|No Lie]]\"\n# \"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n# \"[[Scared to be Lonely]]\"\n# \"Genesis\"\n# \"Be The One\"\n# \"Blow Your Mind (Mwah)\"\n}}\n\n===Opening acts===\n* [[Ro Ransom]] (North America)\n* Off Bloom (Europe)\n\n===Tour dates===\n\n==== North American leg (24 February \u2013 17 March 2017) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/dualipa/status/821371743562514433|title=DUA LIPA on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|24 February 2017\n|[[Chicago]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[United States]]\n|Lincoln Hall\n|-\n|25 February 2017\n|[[Detroit]]\n|{{sort|Shelter, The|The Shelter}}\n|-\n|27 February 2017\n|[[Toronto]]\n|[[Canada]]\n|[[Mod Club Theatre]]\n|-\n|1 March 2017\n|[[New York City]]\n| rowspan=\"12\" |United States\n|[[Irving Plaza]]\n|-\n|2 March 2017\n|[[Philadelphia]]\n|{{sort|Founrdy, The|[[The Fillmore|The Foundry]]}}\n|-\n|4 March 2017\n|[[Boston]]\n|[[Paradise Rock Club]]\n|-\n|5 March 2017\n|[[Washington, D.C.]]\n|Rock & Roll Hotel\n|-\n|7 March 2017\n|[[Atlanta]]\n|The Loft\n|-\n|8 March 2017\n|[[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]]\n|T{{sort|Social, The|The Social}}\n|-\n|9 March 2017\n|[[St. Petersburg, Florida|St. Petersburg]]\n|[[State Theatre (St. Petersburg, Florida)|State Theatre]]\n|-\n|11 March 2017\n|[[Houston]]\n|[[House of Blues]]\n|-\n|12 March 2017\n|[[Dallas]]\n|Prophet Bar\n|-\n|14 March 2017\n|[[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]]\n|Crescent Ballroom\n|-\n|15 March 2017\n|[[Los Angeles]]\n||The Belasco Theater\n|-\n|17 March 2017\n|[[San Francisco]]\n|[[Great American Music Hall]]\n|}\n\n==== European leg (5\u201313 April 2017) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ocnal.com/2017/03/dua-lipa-to-start-european-tour-from.html|title=Dua Lipa to start the European tour from Milan to London|work=Oculus News English|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|5 April 2017\n|Milan\n|Italy\n|Fabrique\n|-\n|7 April 2017\n|Berlin\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Germany\n|Columbia Theater\n|-\n|8 April 2017\n|Cologne\n|Luxor\n|-\n|9 April 2017\n|[[Utrecht]]\n|Netherlands\n|[[TivoliVredenburg]]\n|-\n|12 April 2017\n|Manchester\n| rowspan=\"2\" |England\n|{{sort|Ritz, The|[[The Ritz (Manchester)|The Ritz]]}}\n|-\n|13 April 2017\n|London\n|[[Shepherd's Bush Empire|Shepherds Bush Empire]]\n|}\n\n==The Self-Titled Tour (2017\u20132018)==\n{{Infobox concert|concert_tour_name=The Self-Titled Tour|artist=[[Dua Lipa]]|type=Concert tour|image=File:Self_Titled_Tour.png|image_size=120|border=yes|album=''[[Dua Lipa]]''|start_date={{Start date|2017|10|05|df=yes}}|end_date={{End date|2018|12|18|df=yes}}|number_of_legs=14|number_of_shows={{Plainlist|\n* 49 in Europe\n* 2 in South America\n* 41 in North America\n* 1 in Middle East\n* 11 in Asia\n* 6 in Oceania\n* 110 total\n}}|last_tour=US and Europe Tour<br />(2017)|next_tour=[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)#Tour and live performances|Future Nostalgia Tour]]<br />(2020)|this_tour='''The Self-Titled Tour'''<br />(2017-18)}}'''The Self-Titled Tour''' is the third official concert tour of the English singer Dua Lipa. The tour supports her eponymous debut studio album. The tour began on 5 October 2017 in Brighton, England, and concluded in December of the following year in Denver, United States.\n\n===Background===\nOn 12 May 2017, three weeks before the release of her debut album, Lipa announced the first stage of the dates, consisting of 20 shows across Europe. On 12 September 2017, dates for North and South America were announced. Some additional dates were added.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dualipa.com/north-american-venue-upgrades/|title=North American Venue Upgrades - Dua Lipa|date=2017-09-21|work=Dua Lipa|access-date=2018-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804140622/https://dualipa.com/north-american-venue-upgrades/|archive-date=4 August 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 25 September 2017, following the commercial success of the single \"New Rules\", other dates were added in the United Kingdom. During 2018, Lipa also performed at various festivals internationally.\n\n===Set list===\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=2017 setlist|content=\n#\"[[Hotter than Hell (Dua Lipa song)|Hotter than Hell]]\"\n#\"Dreams\"\n#\"[[No Lie (Sean Paul song)|No Lie]]\"\n#\"[[Lost in Your Light]]\"\n#\"Garden\"\n#\"[[Last Dance (Dua Lipa song)|Last Dance]]\"\n#\"[[IDGAF (Dua Lipa song)|IDGAF]]\"\n#\"[[Blow Your Mind (Mwah)]]\"\n#\"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n#\"New Love\"\n#\"Genesis\"\n#\"No Goodbyes\"\n#\"[[Scared to Be Lonely]]\"\n#\"Begging\"\n;Encore\n#<li value=15>\"[[Homesick (Dua Lipa song)|Homesick]]\"\n#\"[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be the One]]\"\n#\"[[New Rules (song)|New Rules]]\"}}\n{{hidden|headercss=background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|contentcss=text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 50%;|header=2018 setlist|content=\n#\"Blow Your Mind (Mwah)\"\n#\"Dreams\"\n#\"No Lie\"\n#\"My Love\"\n#\"Lost in Your Light\"\n#\"High\"\n#\"Garden\"\n#\"Last Dance\"\n#\"Be the One\"\n#\"[[One Kiss (song)|One Kiss]]\"\n#\"Thinking 'Bout You\"\n#\"New Love\"\n#\"Genesis\"\n#\"Bad Together\"\n#\"Scared to Be Lonely\"\n#\"Homesick\"\n#\"No Goodbyes\"\n#\"Hotter than Hell\"\n#\"Begging\"\n;Encore\n#<li value=20>\"IDGAF\"\n#\"New Rules\"}}\n\n===Opening acts===\n*[[Clairo]] (USA)\n* [[Tommy Genesis]] (USA)\n*[[Marteen]] (USA & Canada)\n* [[Transviolet]] (USA)\n*[[Yoshi Flower]] (USA)\n* [[Off Bloom]] (Europe)\n* [[Grace Carter (singer)|Grace Carter]] (Europe)\n*[[Vic Mensa]] (UK)\n* Col3Trane (UK & Ireland)\n\n===Tour dates===\n\n==== European leg (5\u201313 April 2017) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of tour dates with date, city, country, venue<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dualipa.com/self-titled-tour/|title=THE SELF-TITLED TOUR - Dua Lipa|date=2017-05-12|work=Dua Lipa|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Venue\n|-\n|5 October 2017\n|[[Brighton]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" |England\n|[[Brighton Dome]]\n|-\n|6 October 2017\n|[[Bournemouth]]\n|[[O2 Academy Bournemouth]]\n|-\n|8 October 2017\n|[[Leeds]]\n|[[O2 Academy Leeds]]\n|-\n|10 October 2017\n|[[Manchester]]\n|[[Manchester Academy]]\n|-\n|11 October 2017\n|[[Glasgow]]\n|Scotland\n|[[O2 Academy Glasgow]]\n|-\n|13 October 2017\n|[[Newcastle upon Tyne]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |England\n|[[O2 Academy Newcastle]]\n|-\n|14 October 2017\n|[[Birmingham]]\n|[[O2 Academy Birmingham]]\n|-\n|17 October 2017\n|[[Paris]]\n|[[France]]\n|YOYO\n|-\n|19 October 2017\n|[[Munich]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Germany\n|Backstage Werk\n|-\n|20 October 2017\n|[[Frankfurt]]\n|[[Batschkapp]]\n|-\n|21 October 2017\n|[[Esch-sur-Alzette]]\n|[[Luxembourg]]\n|[[Rockhal]]\n|-\n|24 October 2017\n|[[Cologne]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Germany\n|[[Live Music Hall]]\n|-\n|25 October 2017\n|[[Berlin]]\n|Astra \n|-\n|27 October 2017\n|[[Hamburg]]\n|[[Docks (nightclub)|Docks]]\n|-\n|29 October 2017\n|[[Oslo]]\n|[[Norway]]\n|[[Rockefeller Music Hall]]\n|-\n|1 November 2017\n|[[Copenhagen]]\n|Denmark\n|Amager Bio\n|-\n|3 November 2017\n|[[Antwerp]]\n|[[Belgium]]\n|[[Lotto Arena]]\n|-\n|5 November 2017\n|[[Amsterdam]]\n|Netherlands\n|[[AFAS Live]]\n|-\n|6 November 2017\n|[[London]]\n|England\n|[[O2 Brixton Academy|O2 Academy Brixton]]\n|}\n\n==== South American leg (9\u201313 November 2017) 