{"title_page": "Kayden Kross", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox adult biography\n|name            = Kayden Kross\n|image           = Kayden Kross 2015.jpg\n|caption         = Kross at the [[AVN Adult Entertainment Expo|AVN Expo]] in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]] on January 22, 2015\n|birth_name      = \n|birth_date      = \n|birth_place     = [[Sacramento, California]], [[United States|U.S]]<ref name=AIPDaily>{{cite web|url= http://aipdaily.com/interview-with-kayden-kross/|title= Interview with Kayden Kross|accessdate= July 31, 2008|author= Christina|date= May 21, 2008|publisher= AIPdaily.com|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080727004321/http://aipdaily.com/interview-with-kayden-kross/|archivedate= July 27, 2008|df= mdy-all}}</ref>\n|spouse          = \n|partner         = [[Manuel Ferrara]] (2012\u2013present)\n|children        = 1\n|height          = \n|weight          =\n|alias           = Jenna Nikol, Jenna Nickol, Kayden Cross\n|website         = {{url|clubkayden.com}}\n}}\n'''Kayden Kross''' is an American [[pornographic actress]], [[writer]], and [[Film director|director]].\n\n==Early life==\nKross was born and raised in [[Sacramento, California]]. She grew up in the foothills between Sacramento and [[Placerville, California|Placerville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsreview.com/sacramento/inside-kayden-kross/content?oid=666631|title=Inside Kayden Kross|date=May 22, 2008|work=Sacramento News & Review|accessdate=August 23, 2013}}</ref> She is of mostly Swedish ancestry.<ref name=\"AIPDaily\" /> She has described herself as \"the book [[nerd]]\" during her time as a high school student.<ref name=\"Xcitement\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xcitement.com/interview/?page_id=135 |title=Kayden Kross |accessdate=August 9, 2008 |author=Cindi Loftus |date=March\u2013April 2008 |publisher=Xcitement magazine |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603235758/http://www.xcitement.com/interview/?page_id=135 |archivedate=June 3, 2008 }}</ref> Kross began stripping at Rick's Showgirls in [[Rancho Cordova, California]] when she was eighteen years old to earn extra money to rescue a pony from a slaughter house, which she kept for eight months.<ref name=\"statehornet\">Cody Kitaura {{cite web|url=http://media.www.statehornet.com/media/storage/paper1146/news/2006/11/29/News/From-Bookworm.To.Hot.Hornet-2780487.shtml |title=\"From bookworm to hot hornet\" |accessdate=November 3, 2007 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913235718/http://media.www.statehornet.com/media/storage/paper1146/news/2006/11/29/News/From-Bookworm.To.Hot.Hornet-2780487.shtml |archivedate=September 13, 2008 }}, ''State Hornet'', StateHornet.com (November 29, 2006). Retrieved June 22, 2012.</ref> She was later contacted by an agent, whose business relationship provided Kross with the opportunity of modeling in [[adult magazine]]s.<ref name=adam>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/28756.html|title= Adam & Eve Signs Kayden Kross|accessdate= July 31, 2008|author= Wade Garrett|date= December 18, 2007|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nHer movies with Vivid included ''Kayden's First Time'', ''Hard Time'', and ''Be Here Now''. Unhappy with the company, she became a free agent one year later when she did not renew her contract.<ref name=Xcitement/> She signed an exclusive contract with [[Adam & Eve (business)|Adam & Eve]] after one month of being a free agent.<ref name=adam />\nShe was named ''[[Penthouse (magazine)|Penthouse]]'' [[Pet of the Month]] for September 2008.<ref name=\"KaydenMySpace\">{{cite web|url=https://www.myspace.com/kaydenkross|title=Kayden Kross MySpace profile|accessdate=July 31, 2008|date=July 31, 2008}}</ref> Kross' official website, ClubKayden.com, was launched on September 2, 2008. Kross has hosted a blog at UnKrossed.com, and has written regular updates and opinion columns for MikeSouth.com, an adult industry gossip blog, among other sites.<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/29613.html|title= Kayden Kross Blogs for MikeSouth.com|accessdate= July 31, 2008|author= David Sullivan|date= April 14, 2008|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref>\n\nKross became exclusive to Digital Playground under a multi-year contract on January 1, 2010. Her first movie with the company, ''The Smiths'', topped sales charts immediately and has continued to be a best seller. She was given the lead in their big budget feature, ''Body Heat'', in her third month in contract. She won two Best Actress Awards for the role.<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://news.avn.com/company-news/Digital-Playground-The-Smiths-Tops-Sales-Charts-398480.html|title= Kayden Kross' Digital Playground Debut, 'The Smiths,' Climbs the Charts|accessdate= May 27, 2010<!-- 01:36 PM -->|date= May 27, 2010|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100727094225/http://news.avn.com/company-news/Digital-Playground-The-Smiths-Tops-Sales-Charts-398480.html|archivedate= July 27, 2010|df= mdy-all}}</ref>{{clarify|date=April 2015}}\n\nKross hosted the 2010 [[AVN Award]]s show, along with porn actress [[Kirsten Price (actress)|Kirsten Price]] and comedian [[Dave Attell]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/37031.html|title=Dave Attell to Co-Host AVN Awards|accessdate= December 24, 2009|author= Dan Miller|date= December 23, 2009|magazine= AVN}}</ref> She was ''Penthouse'' magazine's \"Cover Girl\" for September 2008 and 2010.<ref>[http://penthousemagazine.com/issues/2010/penthouse-magazine-september-2010/ Penthouse Magazine September 2010] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101204120330/http://penthousemagazine.com/issues/2010/penthouse-magazine-september-2010/ |date=December 4, 2010 }}. Penthousemagazine.com (September 3, 2010). Retrieved on January 29, 2012.</ref>  Kross starred in the 2010 AVN Best Feature ''The 8th Day'' and portrayed the role of [[Elin Nordegren]], wife of [[Tiger Woods]], in Adam & Eve Pictures' film ''Tyler's Wood''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.gentlemensclubpodcast.com/post/293077564|title= Kayden Kross on the Gentlemen's Club Podcast|accessdate= December 24, 2009|author= Hammer and Bacon|date= December 21, 2009|publisher= [[The Gentlemen's Club With Hammer and Bacon]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, she hosted the Xbiz awards for the second time, and appeared in the ceremony alongside [[Wicked Pictures]]/Wicked.com contract star, [[Jessica Drake]], and on the AVN [[red carpet]] with co-hosts [[Jesse Jane]] and guitarist [[Dave Navarro]].\n\n===Appearances in other media===\nKross has made appearances in the FX's comedy series ''[[The League]]'', the G4 [[reality television|reality series]] ''The Block'', and  ''[[Gene Simmons Family Jewels|Family Jewels]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/5257.html |title=Kayden Kross Featured on 'Family Jewels' |accessdate=July 31, 2008 |author=David Sullivan |date=March 18, 2008 |magazine=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302080015/http://business.avn.com/articles/5257.html |archivedate=March 2, 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2011 she was cast as Tara in [[Gregory Hatanaka]]'s drama ''[[Blue Dream]]''<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1307442/ \"The Obsession (2012)\"]. IMDb.com</ref> briefly co-hosted a regular [[videocast]], ''Kayden's Review'', for [[Triggla TV]]<ref>[http://www.rogreviews.com/28119/kayden-kross-joins-triggla-tv/ Digital Playground's Kayden Kross joins Triggla TV] (July 26, 2011) Retrieved on February 21, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://trigg.la/episodes/kaydens-review/ |title=\u2013 Kayden\u2019s Review |publisher=Trigg.la |date= |accessdate=February 9, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107030936/http://trigg.la/episodes/kaydens-review/ |archive-date=November 7, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> alongside the comedian Dane Hanson.<ref>[http://trigg.la/episodes/kaydens-review/ Kayden's Review on Triggla TV.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107030936/http://trigg.la/episodes/kaydens-review/ |date=November 7, 2017 }} Retrieved on February 21, 2013.</ref> From 2012 - 2013, Kross portrayed a main character in the second season of [[Tucky Williams]]' lesbian-themed web series ''[[Girl/Girl Scene]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Online lesbian drama ''Girl/Girl Scene'', set in Lexington, begins Season 2|url = http://www.kentucky.com/entertainment/tv/article44368131.html|website = kentucky|accessdate = November 30, 2015}}</ref> Starting from January 2013 Kross hosts the weekly [[call-in show]] ''Krossfire'' on [[Playboy Radio]].<ref name=bio>\"Adult Who's Who: Kayden Kross\", ''[[AVN (magazine)|AVN Magazine]]'', Vol. 29/No. 2, Issue 362, February 2013, p.32.</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Kross also appeared in the featurette \"Chicks 'N Guns\" on the ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' 5th season DVD as a stripper. The scene takes place during the season 5 episode \"Gliding Over All.\" Kross also appeared in two music videos from the band [[Nekrogoblikon]], \"No One Survives\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KsMKOx6fumc |title= No One Survives  |publisher= Brandon Dermer |date=September 4, 2012 |accessdate=February 11, 2017}}</ref> in 2012 and \"We Need a Gimmick\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Q3ub1SUYfg |title= we need a gimmick |publisher= Mystery Box |date=June 2, 2015 |accessdate=February 11, 2017}}</ref> in 2015.\n\n===Writing===\nKross writes columns regularly for publications such as ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' magazine, ''[[XBIZ]]'' magazine, and a blog for xcritic.com.<ref>[http://www.complex.com/blogs/2010/12/14/my-spot-kayden-kross-loves-urth-caffe-in-l-a/ My Spot: Kayden Kross Loves Urth Caffe in L.A.]. complex.com (December 14, 2010)</ref><ref>[http://aipdaily.com/2010/kayden-kross-writes-blog-the-inspires-new-xbiz-feature-column/ Kayden Kross Writes Blog the Inspires New XBiz Feature Column] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101210100250/http://aipdaily.com/2010/kayden-kross-writes-blog-the-inspires-new-xbiz-feature-column/ |date=December 10, 2010 }}. AIPdaily.com (November 4, 2010). Retrieved on January 29, 2012.</ref> She has also contributed to ''[[McSweeney's|Timothy McSweeney's Internet Tendency]]'', and her short story \"Plank\" appeared in the 2012 short story collection ''Forty Stories: New Writing from [[Harper Perennial]]'', an e-book. As of August 2012, she was writing an autobiographical book about the porn industry.<ref name=Nazaryan>{{Citation| title = From porn to publishing: The Kross-cultural journey| url = http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/porn-star-kayden-kross-a-stimulating-literary-life-article-1.1138882 | author = Nazaryan, Alexander  | journal = New York Daily News | date = August 20, 2012 | accessdate = August 27, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Adult industry activism===\nIn 2008, she was among those testifying against a proposed tax in California on all producers and distributors of adult entertainment.<ref name=\"Steinhauer-0508\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/05/26/us/26porn.html?pagewanted=print|title=California Lawmaker Proposes Tax on Sex Industry|last=Steinhauer|first=Jennifer|date=May 28, 2008|newspaper=New York Times|accessdate=January 3, 2010}}</ref> In February 2012, she and [[Conservatism in the United States|conservative]] pundit Wendy Murphy appeared on ''[[Stossel (TV series)|Stossel]]'', with host [[John Stossel]], to discuss legislation in California that would require that [[condom]]s be used during the production of adult movies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Editor's Picks: Policing the Porn Business|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/1457167903001|work=FOX Business|publisher=FOX News Network, LLC|accessdate=June 7, 2012|author=Editor|format=Video file|date=February 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn October 2008, Kross was [[Criminal charge|charged]] with [[grand theft]] and violations of the California Civil Code, involving contracts for purchases of [[home equity]] mortgages.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://avn.com/business/articles/video/kayden-kross-charged-in-mortgage-scam-54827.html|title= Kayden Kross Charged in Mortgage Scam|accessdate= September 17, 2008|date= September 17, 2008|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref> In July 2009, the grand-theft charge was dismissed, and the real-estate-fraud charge was reduced to a misdemeanor; Kross pleaded [[no contest]] to the resulting charges and was sentenced to one day in custody and three years of [[probation]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.xbiz.com/news/110039|title= Kayden Kross Pleads No Contest in Real Estate Case|accessdate= July 5, 2009|author= Tod Hunter|date= July 2, 2009|publisher= XBiz}}</ref> She blamed her involvement in the situation on her na\u00efvet\u00e9 and being scammed by the broker and mortgage lender.<ref>[http://business.avn.com/articles/Kayden-Kross-Victim-of-Mortgage-Scam-Pleads-No-Contest-349258.html AVN \u2013 Kayden Kross, Victim of Mortgage Scam, Pleads 'No Contest']. Business.avn.com (July 6, 2009). Retrieved on January 29, 2012.</ref>\n\nKross and her French partner [[Manuel Ferrara]] have one daughter, born in January 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.nerve.com/entertainment/this-porn-star-is-the-hottest-and-smartest-person-in-the-room |title=10 Reasons Kayden Kross Is the Hottest and Smartest Porn Star in the Room |publisher=Nerve.com |date=June 18, 2009 |accessdate=February 9, 2014}}</ref> In 2013, Ferrara asked her to no longer perform with other men.<ref name=\"abcnews\">{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/lifestyle/2014/11/my-fianc-is-a-porn-star-and-im-okay-with-it/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150315143414/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/lifestyle/2014/11/my-fianc-is-a-porn-star-and-im-okay-with-it/|archive-date=March 15, 2015|title=My Fianc\u00e9 Is a Porn Star and I\u2019m Okay With It|last=ABC News|date=November 13, 2014|work=ABC News|accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n[[File:Kayden Kross 2009.jpg|thumb|200px| Kayden Kross attending at the \"Free Speech Coalition Awards Annual Bash Event\" - Los Angeles, on November 14, 2009.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Film\n|-\n|2009\n|[[Hot d'Or]]\n|Best American Starlet<ref>{{cite web|author=Paul Fishbein|title=Pirates II, Evil Angel Big Winners at 2009 Hot d\u2019Or Awards|work=AVN|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/36568.html|date=October 21, 2009|accessdate=October 21, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hot-dor.fr/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=2&Itemid=4 |title=Hot d\u2019Or archives presse x, articles sur les Hot d\u2019or |publisher=Hot-dor.fr |accessdate=May 9, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140316035017/http://hot-dor.fr/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=2&Itemid=4 |archivedate=March 16, 2014 }}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2010\n|[[Venus Award]]\n|Best Actress International<ref>[http://www.venus-berlin.com/download/venus.2010.award.gewinner.de.pdf Venus 2010 Award Winners]. venus-berlin.com  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101121230409/http://www.venus-berlin.com/download/venus.2010.award.gewinner.de.pdf |date=November 21, 2010 }}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|-\n|[[Erotixxx Award]]\n|Best U.S. Actress<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.erofame.eu/en/erotixxx-award/2010 |title=EROTIX Award 2010 - the winners &#124; eroFame 2014 |publisher=Erofame.eu |accessdate=February 9, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101115533/https://www.erofame.eu/en/erotixxx-award/2010 |archivedate=November 1, 2013  }}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|-\n|[[NightMoves Award]]\n|Best Female Performer (Fan's Choice)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/NightMoves-Announces-2010-Awards-Winners-415547.html|title=NightMoves Announces 2010 Awards Winners|last=Steve J