s of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Dominican Republic descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Hungarian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Ashkenazi Jews]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tisch School of the Arts alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress writer and singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=November 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image         = Juliana Harkavy, 2017 (cropped).jpg\n| caption       = Harkavy in 2017\n| name          = Juliana Harkavy\n| birth_name    = Juliana Jay Harkavy\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1985|1|1}}\n| birth_place   = New York City\n| occupation    = Actress, writer, musician\n| years_active  = 1996\u2013present\n| notable_works = ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]''\n| spouse        = {{married|Peter Christopher Kupchick|2014}}\n}}\n\n'''Juliana Jay Harkavy'''<ref name=marriage>{{cite web|url=https://www.fairfieldcitizenonline.com/news/article/Wedding-Kupchick-Harkavy-5748868.php|title=Wedding / Kupchick-Harkavy|publisher=\"Fairfield Citizen\"|date=September 11, 2014}}</ref> (born January 1, 1985) is an American actress, writer, and singer. She is known for portraying Rebecca in ''[[Dolphin Tale]]'', Jessie in ''[[Day One (2012 film)|To Write Love on her Arms]]'', and [[List of The Walking Dead (TV series) characters#Martinez's group|Alisha]] in the television series ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''.  Her roles include a starring role in the [[horror film]] ''[[Last Shift]]'', and a reprise of her role as Rebecca in ''[[Dolphin Tale 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2013/10/18/dolphin-tale-2-filming-underway-at-clearwater-aquarium/ |title='Dolphin Tale 2' filming underway at Clearwater Aquarium |publisher=On Location Vacations |date=October 18, 2013 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Goldberg |first=Matt |url=https://collider.com/renee-movie-image-set-photo/ |title=RENEE Movie Image and Set Photo |publisher=Collider |date=February 16, 2012 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/06/anthony-deblasi-directing-horror-pic-paymon/ |title=Anthony DiBlasi Directing Horror Pic \u2018Paymon\u2019 |publisher=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 28, 2013 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/photo/juliana-harkavy-the-los-angeles-premiere-of-dolphin-tale-at-the-mann_3518761 |title=Picture \u2013 Juliana Harkavy Los Angeles, California, Saturday 17th September 2011 &#124; Photo 2588460 |publisher=Contactmusic.com |date=September 17, 2011 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reneethemovie.com/cast.html |title=Meet The Cast |publisher=Reneethemovie.com |accessdate=August 2, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202223432/http://www.reneethemovie.com/cast.html |archivedate=December 2, 2013 }}</ref> She was a series regular on [[The CW]] superhero series ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'', portraying [[Dinah Drake (Arrowverse)|Dinah Drake / Black Canary]].<ref name=\"Crucible ep\">{{cite episode|title=Second Chances|series=Arrow|credits=Speed Weed & Sarah Tarkoff (writers) & Mark Bunting (director)|network=The CW|airdate=February 1, 2017|season=5|number=11}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHarkavy was born in New York City. She is the daughter of Berta Carela and Michael Harkavy, who is the former Senior Vice president of [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Entertainment]] Worldwide Publishing, [[Kids' WB]] Music, and [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]].{{citation needed|date=November 2017}} Her professional acting career began when she was 10 years old.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}} Harkavy has described herself as \"a [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] [[Jew]]\", although her mother was born [[Catholic]].<ref>https://mobile.twitter.com/JulianaHarkavy/status/512376226825371648</ref><ref>https://www.instagram.com/julianaharkavy/p/BSuKKOBjOhd/</ref> She also said that her paternal ancestors were from Russia and Hungary, whereas her maternal ancestors were from the Dominican Republic, Africa, and China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JulianaHarkavy/status/829135942556405760|title=That's right! That's mom's side. Pops is Russian/Hungarian |publisher=Twitter|date=February 7, 2017}}{{Primary source inline|date=October 2019}}</ref>\n\nHarkavy trained at the [[Young Actors Space]] in [[Sherman Oaks, California]] for nine years. She attended her first year of high school at [[Le Lyc\u00e9e Fran\u00e7ais de Los Angeles]], where she became fluent in French,{{citation needed|date=November 2017}} and did part of her schooling in the South of France. She earned her high school diploma from the [[Milken Community High School]] in Los Angeles, California.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}After high school, Harkavy attended The [[Tisch School of the Arts]] at [[New York University]], where she majored in Theater in the Sanford Meisner studio.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3952890/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm|title=ABCD|publisher=IMDb|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHarkavy's first acting job was at age 10 in a commercial for the [[Fox Kids]] series ''[[Goosebumps (TV series)|Goosebumps]]'', based on the popular horror-book series.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}} Her first role in a major motion picture was an uncredited role in the 1995 version of ''[[A Little Princess (1995 film)|A Little Princess]]'', directed by [[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]].{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\nHarkavy starred in the 2011 film ''If You Only Knew'' about early-onset [[Alzheimer's Disease]]. She stars as Jessica Loren in the [[horror film]] ''[[Last Shift]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fearnet.com/news/news-article/character-poster-paymon |title=Chiller &#124; Scary Good |publisher=Fearnet.com |date=July 29, 2015 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Ryan|last=Turek |url=http://www.shocktillyoudrop.com/news/174643-first-official-image-from-anthony-diblasis-paymon/ |title=First Official Image from Anthony DiBlasi's Paymon |publisher=Shock Till You Drop |date=June 25, 2013 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://horrorcultfilms.co.uk/2013/07/character-one-sheets-released-for-dread-directors-unique-sounding-chiller-paymon/ |title=Character one-sheets released for Dread director's unique sounding chiller \u2018Paymon\u2019 \" Horror Cult Films \u2013 Movie Reviews of Obscure, Weird, Strange, Horror and Cult Cinema |publisher=Horror Cult Films |date=July 10, 2013 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nHarkavy starred in the 2010 short film ''[[Whatever Lola Wants (film)|Whatever Lola Wants]]''. Nominated for a Best Actress Award at the 2011 [[University of Miami]] Canes Film Festival<ref>{{cite web|url=http://canesfilmfest.moonfruit.com/ |title=Canes Film Festival |accessdate=February 17, 2017}}</ref>\nHarkavy is the star in the short film ''The Lost Doll'' directed by James Walhberg.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rumbumstudios.com/uncategorized/the-lost-doll-short-film-co-produced-by-jim-wahlberg-and-rum-bum-film-hd-studios/  |title= The Lost Doll Short Film PSA Commercial| accessdate=February 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nHarkavy plays Alisha, a survivor involved with the Governor on ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''. She appeared in two episodes: \"Dead Weight\" and \"Too Far Gone\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Dessner |first=Dina |url=http://geekleagueofamerica.com/2013/12/01/geek-league-interview-juliana-harkavy-alicia-on-the-walking-dead/ |title=Geek League Interview \u2013 Juliana Harvkavy, \"Alisha\" On 'The Walking Dead' |publisher=Geek League of America |date=December 1, 2013 |accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 she was cast in the [[Arrow (season 5)|fifth season]] of the [[The CW|CW]] show ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'', in the recurring role of Detective Tina Boland,<ref>[http://tvline.com/2016/11/01/arrow-cast-detective-boland-juliana-harkavy/ \"TVLine Items:Arrow's New Detective\"] \"TVLine\". Retrieved December 28, 2016.</ref> whose true name is revealed to be [[Dinah Drake (Arrowverse)|Dinah Drake]], acting as the new [[Black Canary]].<ref name=\"Crucible ep\"/> She was promoted to series regular for the show's [[Arrow (season 6)|sixth season]], which began airing in the fall of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/arrow-rick-gonzalez-juliana-harkavy-wild-dog-black-canary-promoted-season-6-regulars-1202068856/|title=Arrow Ups Rick Gonzalaz & Juliana Harkavy To Season 6 Regulars|publisher=\"Deadline Hollywood\"|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nOn June 19, 2014, she married Peter Christopher Kupchick (son of State Rep. [[Brenda Kupchick]] and Peter Kupchick).<ref name=marriage/>\n\nShe has lived in New York, [[New Mexico]], [[New Jersey]], California, Florida, and France.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\nShe plays the piano, the guitar, and the flute.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n\n===Film===\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[A Little Princess (1995 film)|A Little Princess]]''\n| Girl in India\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Flushed''\n| Groupie\n| Short\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2006\n| ''Love is Blind''\n| Crystal\n|\n|-\n| ''[[My Super Ex-Girlfriend]]'' \n| Passerby\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Whatever Lola Wants''\n| Lola\n| Short movie, nominated for Best Actress Award at UM Canes film festival.\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2011\n| ''[[Dolphin Tale]]''\n| Rebecca\n| \n|-\n| ''If You Only Knew''\n| Louise\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''A Feeling from Within''\n| Stacey\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2013\n| ''Finding Joy''\n| Pretty Young Woman\n| \n|-\n| ''[[House of Bodies]]''\n| Tisha\n| \n|-\n| ''Marriage Material''\n| Madeline\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=2|2014\n| ''[[Dolphin Tale 2]]''\n| Rebecca\n|\n|- \n|''[[Last Shi