tury American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of African descent]]\n[[Category:American actresses of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Dominican Republic descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Hungarian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Ashkenazi Jews]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tisch School of the Arts alumni]]\n", "name_user": "StrongDonnie0511", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juliana_Harkavy"}
{"title_page": "Acharya Vidyasagar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox religious biography\n| honorific-prefix = ''Sant Shiromani Acharya Shri'' 108\n| name = Vidyasagar\n| honorific-suffix = ''Ji Maharaj''\n| image = Acharya5 (cropped).jpg\n| alt = VIDHYADHAR\n| caption = Acharya Vidyasagar, a prominent ''[[Digambara monk]]''\n| religion = [[Jainism]]\n| sect = ''[[Digambara]]''\n| birth_name = Vidyadhar\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|10|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sadalga]], [[Belgaum district]], [[Karnataka]]\n| father = Mallappa (name after diksha-Mallinath ji)\n| mother = Shrimanti(name after diksha-Samaymati Ji)\n| initiation_date = 30 June 1968\n| initiation_place = [[Ajmer]]\n| initiator = ''Acharya'' [[Gyansagar]]\n| predecessor = ''muni\"[[Gyansagar]]\n| disciples = [[Pramansagar]], [[Sudhasagar]], [[Kshamasagar]], [[Guptisagar]]\n| works = ''Mukamati'' (silent soil)\n| website = {{URL|https://vidyasagar.guru}}\n}}\n{{Jainism}}\n'''Acharya Shri Vidyasagarji Maharaj''' (born 10 October 1946) is one of the best-known modern ''[[Digambara]]'' Jain ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' (Digambar Jain Monk). He is recognized both for his scholarship and ''[[tapasya]]'' (austerity). He is known for his long hours in meditation. While he was born in Karnataka and took ''[[diksha]]'' (undertook spiritual discipline) in [[Rajasthan]], he generally spends much of his time in the [[Bundelkhand]] region where he is credited with having brought about a revival in educational and religious activities.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/religion/story/20021125-aggressive-movement-to-revive-jainism-sweeps-central-india-794269-2002-11-25 |title=Aggressive movement to revive Jainism sweeps central India |first=Neeraj |last=Mishra |work=[[India Today]] |date=25 November 2002 |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925025751/https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/religion/story/20021125-aggressive-movement-to-revive-jainism-sweeps-central-india-794269-2002-11-25 |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He has written [[Haiku]] poems and the epic Hindi poem \"Mukamati\". His life is the subject of the 2018 documentary film ''Vidyoday'' released by [[Landmarc Films|Landmark Films]].\n\n==Life==\n===Early Life===\n\nVidyasagar was born on 10 October 1946 during the full moon festival (''[[Sharad Purnima]]''} in [[Sadalga]], in the [[Belgaum district]], of [[Karnataka]]. \n\nHis childhood name was Vidyadhar.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=23, 35}} He was the second of four sons, the eldest son being Mahavira Ashtage.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=34-35}} As a child, he was fond of eating fresh butter which was used to make [[ghee]] (clarified butter).{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=37}} He was not a demanding child and accepted what was given to him.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=40}} Vidyadhar used to visit temples and teach his younger siblings the principles of religion.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=41-42}} He called both younger sisters ''\"Akka\"'' (elder sister). He was attentive and was eager to undertake his studies. In his spare time he used to paint.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=42}}\n\n===Initiation===\nHe was initiated as a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' in 1968 at the age of 22 by Acharya [[Gyansagar]], who belonged to the lineage of Acharya [[Shantisagar]], at [[Ajmer]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=28}} His father Mallappa, his mother Shrimati, and two sisters took ''diksha'' and joined the ''[[sangha (Jainism)|sangha]]'' (community of the pious) of Acharya Dharmasagar.{{sfn|Gita Jain|1978|pp=8-14}} Except for his eldest brother, his remaining brothers, Anantanath and Shantinath, followed him and were initiated by Acharya Vidyasagar as Muni Yogasagar and Muni Samaysagar respectively.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=73}} His elder brother married and continued the blood line.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/when-acharya-vidyasagar-had-secretly-listen-to-vinoba-bhave-1317790 |title=\u091c\u092c \u091b\u093f\u092a\u0915\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0928\u094b\u092c\u093e \u092d\u093e\u0935\u0947 \u0915\u094b \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0928\u0947 \u0917\u090f \u0925\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 |work=Patrika |date=8 June 2016 |access-date=18 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514142120/https://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/when-acharya-vidyasagar-had-secretly-listen-to-vinoba-bhave-1317790/ |archive-date=14 May 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe was elevated to the ''Acharya'' status in 1972.{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}} An Acharya does not eat salt, sugar, fruits, milk, in addition to what is traditionally prohibited (like onions). He goes out for a meal at about 9:30&nbsp;a.m.\u201310:00&nbsp;a.m. from ''[[\u015ar\u0101vaka (Jainism)|\u015ar\u0101vakas]]'' (lay votaries). He takes food once a day in the palm of his hand, one morsel at a time.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/damoh/amazing-rules-and-rituals-of-acharya-shri-vidhyasagar-ki-aharchariya-1315343/ |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0906\u0939\u093e\u0930\u091a\u0930\u094d\u092f\u093e \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0938\u091c\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u091a\u094c\u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0902, \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u093f\u0928 \u091a\u0940\u091c\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u0947\u0916 \u091b\u094b\u0921\u093c \u0926\u0947\u0924\u0947 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0916\u093e\u0928\u093e, Patrika, 2016-06-05 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327235123/http://www.patrika.com/news/damoh/amazing-rules-and-rituals-of-acharya-shri-vidhyasagar-ki-aharchariya-1315343/ |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn 1999, then Prime Minister [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji during his visit to <!--[http://www.indorerocks.com/attractions/attraction/Gomatgiri/10028---> Gomatgiri Indore.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/shri-atal-bihari-vaypayee-ji-had-visited-acharyashree-in-gomtagiri-indore/|title=Video : \u0938\u0928\u094d 1999 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0905\u091f\u0932 \u092c\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093e\u092f\u092a\u0947\u092f\u0940 \u091c\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u0917\u094b\u092e\u094d\u092e\u091f\u0917\u093f\u0930\u093f \u0907\u0902\u0926\u094c\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u0915\u093f\u090f \u0925\u0947|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503090356/http://www.vidyasagar.net/shri-atal-bihari-vaypayee-ji-had-visited-acharyashree-in-gomtagiri-indore/|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Jain_inscription_Vidyasagar.jpg|thumb|alt= Photograph showing the inscription oin a Parshvanath idol | Inscription on a Parshvanath idol at Orchha mentioning the lineage of Acharya Vidyasagar from Acharya Shantisagar. He is termed ''anasakta yogi'', ''jyeshtha'', ''shreshtha'', ''sant shiromani'']]\n\nAcharya Vidyasagar's ''[[Chaturmas]]'' (four month stay) in 2016 was in [[Bhopal]], [[Madhya Pradesh]],<ref>{{citation |url=http://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-acharya-vidyasagar-thief-arrested-four-female-chef-program-seized-seven-gold-chain-786987 |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u093e\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093f\u0932\u093e \u091a\u094b\u0930 \u0917\u093f\u0930\u092b\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0930, \u0938\u093e\u0924 \u0938\u094b\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u091a\u0948\u0928 \u091c\u092a\u094d\u0924 |work=[[Nai Duniya]] |date=27 July 2016 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728165237/http://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-acharya-vidyasagar-thief-arrested-four-female-chef-program-seized-seven-gold-chain-786987 |archive-date=28 July 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> where he was accompanied by 38 ''munis''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3kd0xm2NMXhUFc5YnZydWVyNFk/view |title=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Sangh Parichaya book 2016.pdf |access-date=28 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413235707/https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3kd0xm2NMXhUFc5YnZydWVyNFk/view |archive-date=13 April 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He gave his ''[[Pravachana]]'' (reading) in the [[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] by special invitation from [[Chief Minister of Madhya Pradesh|Chief Minister]] [[Shivraj Singh Chouhan]] on 28 July 2016.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/bhopal/jain-saint-vidya-sagar-to-give-spiritual-speech-in-mp-assembly-1360946 |title=\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u0947 \u0907\u0924\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0928\u093e\u090f \u0930\u0916\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u092a\u0915\u094d\u0937-\u0935\u093f\u092a\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u0938\u093e\u0925 \u0915\u093e\u092e \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902: \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 |work=[[Rajasthan Patrika]] |date=28 July 2016 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803205001/http://www.patrika.com/news/bhopal/jain-saint-vidya-sagar-to-give-spiritual-speech-in-mp-assembly-1360946/ |archive-date=3 August 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/08/29/when-another-jain-monk-addressed-a-state-legislative-assembly-an |title=When Another Jain Monk Addressed A State Legislative Assembly And There Was No Controversy |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=29 August 2016 |access-date=31 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160830162242/http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/08/29/when-another-jain-monk-addressed-a-state-legislative-assembly-an/ |archive-date=30 August 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2016, during a trip to Bhopal, Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] visited him.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/why-is-modi-keen-to-meet-acharya-vidyasagar/story-3ZbjQ5aVjnSy3NfrVQhUdK.html |title=Why is Modi keen to meet Acharya Vidyasagar? |last=Ranjan |location=[[Bhopal]] |date=14 October 2016 |access-date=17 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017172340/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/why-is-modi-keen-to-meet-acharya-vidyasagar/story-3ZbjQ5aVjnSy3NfrVQhUdK.html |archive-date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was also visited by former Union minister [[Jyotiraditya Scindia]] from the opposing Congress Party.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.freepressjournal.in/bhopal/scindia-makes-up-his-mind-to-lead-congress-in-state/941057 |title=Scindia makes up his mind to lead Congress in state, Sep 29, 2016 |access-date=28 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028084044/http://www.freepressjournal.in/bhopal/scindia-makes-up-his-mind-to-lead-congress-in-state/941057 |archive-date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nCongress State President [[Kamal Nath]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji during his visit to [[Jabalpur]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.palpalindia.com/2018/08/01/jabalpur-mp-Khajuraho-Acharya-Vidyasagar-Maharaj-Arishwad-Kamal-Nath-Hindi-Ashoshagaye-Goshala-news-in-hindi-248694.html|title=\u0916\u091c\u0941\u0930\u093e\u0939\u094b \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0938\u0947 \u0906\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0940\u0935\u093e\u0926 \u0932\u0947\u0928\u0947 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0947 \u0915\u092e\u0932\u0928\u093e\u0925, \u091c\u092c\u0932\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0902\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938\u091c\u0928 news in hindi|work=palpalindia|language=hindi|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503090422/http://www.palpalindia.com/2018/08/01/jabalpur-mp-Khajuraho-Acharya-Vidyasagar-Maharaj-Arishwad-Kamal-Nath-Hindi-Ashoshagaye-Goshala-news-in-hindi-248694.html|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/kamalnath-acharyashri-darshan/|title=\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u093e\u0902\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \u0905\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u0915\u092e\u0932\u0928\u093e\u0925 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u0917\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011190548/http://www.vidyasagar.net/kamalnath-acharyashri-darshan/|archive-date=11 October 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nUnion Minister [[Uma Bharti|Uma Bharati]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji at the completion of 50 years of initiation at the Samyama Swarna Mahotsav festival.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/sagar/news/latest-khajuraho-news-041003-2232493.html|title=\u0915\u0947\u0902\u0926\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0909\u092e\u093e\u092d\u093e\u0930\u0924\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0938\u0947 \u0916\u091c\u0941\u0930\u093e\u0939\u094b \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u093e\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u093e \u0906\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=2018-12-03|language=hi|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005731/https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/sagar/news/latest-khajuraho-news-041003-2232493.html|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> During the [[Guru Purnima]] Celebration in 2018, [[Digvijaya Singh|Digvijay Singh]] received the blessings of Acharya Vidyasagar Ji in [[Chhatarpur]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patrika.com/chhatarpur-news/digvijay-singh-blesses-acharya-vidyasagarji-gurupurnima-3170044/|title=\u0926\u093f\u0917\u094d\u0935\u093f\u091c\u092f \u0938\u093f\u0902\u0939 \u0928\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923\u093f\u092e\u093e \u092a\u0930 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u0938\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0906\u0936\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0926|work=www.patrika.com|language=hindi|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503105256/https://www.patrika.com/chhatarpur-news/digvijay-singh-blesses-acharya-vidyasagarji-gurupurnima-3170044/|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2018, American ambassador [[Kenneth Juster]] paid a visit to Acharya Vidyasagar Ji and assured him he would follow a full [[Vegetarianism|vegetarian]] diet for one day a week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/bhopal/news/american-ambassador-junkie-influenced-by-acharya-vidyasagar-5926529.html|title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0938\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u092d\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u0941\u090f \u0905\u092e\u0947\u0930\u093f\u0915\u0940 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u0926\u0942\u0924 \u091c\u0938\u094d\u091f\u0930; \u0915\u0939\u093e- \u0939\u092b\u094d\u0924\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u090f\u0915 \u0926\u093f\u0928 \u0930\u0939\u0942\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0936\u093e\u0915\u093e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u0940|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=2018-12-03|language=hi|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005700/https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/bhopal/news/american-ambassador-junkie-influenced-by-acharya-vidyasagar-5926529.html|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> French Diplomat [[Alexandre Ziegler]] visited [[Khajuraho Group of Monuments|Khajuraho]] with his family in 2018 and felt \"peaceful and blessed\" after meeting Acharya Vidyasagar Ji. He vowed to become a vegetarian.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/french-diplomat-vows-to-turn-veggie-after-meeting-jain-muni/articleshow/66397413.cms|title=French diplomat vows to turn vegetarian after meeting Jain muni - Times of India|work=[[The Times of India]]|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref>\n\n[[Uttar Pradesh]] Chief Minister [[Yogi Adityanath]] has declared the State Guest Honour to Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj. In this regard, the UP Government also issued a protocol.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.patrika.com/lalitpur-news/acharya-vidyasagar-ji-will-be-honoured-with-rajkiya-atithi-samman-3727424/|title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u094b \u0930\u093e\u091c\u0915\u0940\u092f \u0905\u0924\u093f\u0925\u093f \u0938\u092e\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928, \u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0918\u094b\u0937\u0923\u093e|work=www.patrika.com|access-date=2018-11-27|language=hi-IN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181126004003/https://www.patrika.com/lalitpur-news/acharya-vidyasagar-ji-will-be-honoured-with-rajkiya-atithi-samman-3727424/|archive-date=26 November 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nUnion Home Minister Shri [[Rajnath Singh|Rajnath Singh Ji]] has taken the blessings of Acharya Vidyasagar Ji in [[Jabalpur]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/rajnathsingh/status/1119921007605760000|title=\u092e\u0927\u094d\u092f \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u0941\u0928\u093e\u0935\u0940 \u0926\u094c\u0930\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0935\u094d\u092f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0924\u093e\u0913\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u092c\u0940\u091a \u092e\u0941\u091d\u0947 \u0906\u091c \u091c\u0948\u0928 \u092e\u0941\u0928\u093f, \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930\u091c\u0940  \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u094c\u092d\u093e\u0917\u094d\u092f \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e\u0964 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u0930\u0923\u094b\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094b\u091f\u093f\u0936: \u0928\u092e\u0928!pic.twitter.com/j4c5wPTn4N|last=Singh|first=Chowkidar Rajnath|date=2019-04-21|website=@rajnathsingh|language=hi|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\n[[Lok Sabha]] Speaker [[Om Birla]] has taken the blessings of Acharya Vidyasagar Ji with an assurance of Hindi Promotion in Legislature.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naidunia.com/madhya-pradesh/dewas-acharya-vidyasagar-told-the-speaker-of-lok-sabha-hindi-should-be-used-in-parliament-speak-bharat-not-india-3121184|title=\u0932\u094b\u0915\u0938\u092d\u093e \u0905\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u0938\u0947 \u092c\u094b\u0932\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 : \u0938\u0902\u0938\u0926 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0939\u094b \u0905\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u094b \u0907\u0902\u0921\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u092d\u093e\u0930\u0924 \u092c\u094b\u0932\u0947\u0902|date=2019-08-29|website=Nai Dunia|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n[[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh|RSS]] Chief [[Mohan Bhagwat]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji during his visit he discussed various topics related to Promotion of Hindi Language and handloom were discussed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/indore/news/mohan-bhagwat-meets-digambara-jain-acharya-vidyasagar-in-indore-lavkush-vidya-vihar-school-126459015.html|title=\u0938\u0902\u0918 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0941\u0916 \u092d\u093e\u0917\u0935\u0924 \u0928\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0938\u0947 \u0906\u0936\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0926 \u0932\u093f\u092f\u093e, \u0939\u0925\u0915\u0930\u0918\u093e \u0914\u0930 \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092d\u093e\u0937\u093e \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0902\u092c\u0902\u0927 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u0930\u094d\u091a\u093e \u0915\u0940|last=Tiwari|first=Rajeev kumar|date=2020-01-08|website=Dainik Bhaskar|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nMadhya Pradesh CM [[Kamal Nath]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji and assured the promotion of Hindi Language, Ayurveda and handloom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naidunia.com/madhya-pradesh/indore-acharya-vidyasagar-spoke-to-cm-kamal-nath-handloom-and-ayurveda-need-encouragement-5288951|title=\u0938\u0940\u090f\u092e \u0915\u092e\u0932\u0928\u093e\u0925 \u0938\u0947 \u092c\u094b\u0932\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0939\u0925\u0915\u0930\u0918\u093e \u0914\u0930 \u0906\u092f\u0941\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0947\u0926 \u0915\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u093e\u0939\u0928 \u0915\u0940 \u0906\u0935\u0936\u094d\u092f\u0915\u0924\u093e|date=2020-01-26|website=Nai Dunia|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n* Acharya Vidyasagara is a scholar of [[Sanskrit]] and [[Prakrit]] and knows several languages including [[Hindi]] and [[Kannada]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=26}} He has written in languages such as Prakrit, Sanskrit, Hindi. His works include ''Niranjana Shataka'', ''Bhavana Shataka'', ''Parishah Jaya Shataka'', ''Suniti Shataka'' and ''Shramana Shataka''.<ref>Ek Tapahput kavi ki kavya Sadhna, Asha Malaiya, Tirthankar, Nov-Dec 78, p. 21-24</ref> \n* He has composed nearly 700 [[haiku]] poems which are unpublished.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.pinterest.com/vidyasagar_guru/haiku-poems-by-acharya-vidyasagar-ji/|title=Haiku Poems by Acharya Vidyasagar Ji|website=Pinterest|language=en|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/haiku-17265/|title=\u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|access-date=2018-11-02|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807091030/http://www.vidyasagar.net/haiku-17265/|archive-date=7 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vidyasagar.guru/haiku/|title=\u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942 \u0938\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0927\u094d\u092f\u093e\u092f - \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942 \u0914\u0930 \u0906\u092a\u0915\u0940 \u0938\u092e\u091d - \u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|website=\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005632/https://vidyasagar.guru/haiku/|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* He wrote the Hindi epic poem \"Mukamati\".{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}}<ref name=\"webindia2\" /> This has been included in the syllabus of Hindi MA programmes at various institutions.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MPc-58-1943771-NOR.html |title=\u092c\u0940\u092f\u0942 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u093f\u0932\u0947\u092c\u0938 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091c\u0948\u0928 \u0917\u094d\u0930\u0902\u0925 '\u092e\u0942\u0915\u092e\u093e\u091f\u0940' \u0915\u094b \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=24 May 2013 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308234934/http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MPc-58-1943771-NOR.html |archive-date=8 March 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This has been translated into English by <!--[https://www.jainworld.com/society/speaksch/dalchand.htm---> Lal Chandra Jain and was presented to the [[President of India]].<ref name=\"webindia2\" /><ref name=\"jainworld.com\">{{citation|url=http://jainworld.com/GJE.asp?id=54|title=Acharya Vidyasagar's Book \"Silent Earth\" Presented To President|work=jainworld.com|access-date=10 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316143001/http://jainworld.com/GJE.asp?id=54|archive-date=16 March 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>{{sfn|Vidyasagar|2010|p=}} Several researchers have studied his works for masters and doctoral degrees.<ref name=\"webindia2\">{{citation |url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20110615/1772295.html |title=Acharya Vidyasagar's book \"Silent Earth\" presented to President |work=[[Web India 123]] |date=15 June 2011 |access-date=12 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163303/http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20110615/1772295.html |archive-date=14 July 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n<!--<blockquote>\u0926\u094b \u0939\u093f\u0924 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0928\u093f\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u094b\u0902, \u0935\u0939 '\u0926\u0941\u0939\u093f\u0924\u093e' \u0915\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948<br />\u0905\u092a\u0928\u093e \u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u094d\u0935\u092f\u0902 \u0939\u0940 \u0915\u0930 \u0932\u0947\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948, \u092a\u0924\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u0947 \u092a\u0924\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093e \u091c\u0940\u0935\u0928 \u092d\u0940<br />\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u0947 \u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u094b\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0938\u0947 \u0935\u0939 '\u0926\u0941\u0939\u093f\u0924\u093e' \u0915\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964 <br />\u0906\u0908\u092f\u0947\u2026\u0910\u0938\u0940 \u092c\u0947\u091f\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u093e\u0925 \u092e\u093f\u0932\u0915\u0930 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u2026<br />\u090f\u0915 \u0913\u0930\u2026'\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928'   An excerpt from ''Mukamati (\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928)''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/betiyan/|title=\u092c\u0947\u091f\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0901|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|access-date=2018-12-04|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205004740/http://www.vidyasagar.net/betiyan/|archive-date=5 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref></blockquote>  This should be translated into English if it is to be included in the article.--->\n\n==His tradition==\nAcharya Vidyasagar belongs to the tradition established by Acharya [[Shantisagar]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=51}} Acharya Shantisagar initiated Acharya Virasagar, who was then succeeded by Acharya Shivsagar, Acharya [[Gyansagar]]<ref>{{citation |title=\u0907\u0938 \u0938\u0902\u0924 \u0915\u0947 \u091c\u0940\u0935\u0924 \u0930\u0939\u0924\u0947 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0942\u0921\u0947\u0902\u091f \u0915\u0930 \u0930\u0939\u0947 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0907\u0928 \u092a\u0930 PHD, \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094d\u092f\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0907\u0928\u0915\u0940 \u0916\u0942\u092c\u0940 |url=http://m.bhaskar.com/news/c-58-3193036-bp0851-NOR.html |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=17 October 2016 |access-date=28 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028215045/http://m.bhaskar.com/news/c-58-3193036-bp0851-NOR.html |archive-date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>and finally Acharya Vidyasagar.\n\nSome of his disciples are well-known scholars in their own right. {{As of|2001}}, about 21% of all the ''Digambar'' monks were under Acharya Vidyasagara.{{sfn|Fl\u00fcgel|2006|p=356}} Muni [[Sudhasagar]] and Muni [[Pramansagar]] are also his disciples.<ref>{{citation |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Jain-Muni-Pramansagar-ji-Maharaj-disciple-of-Acharya-Vidyasagar-ji-Maharaj-would-discourse-on-Ramayana-and-Geeta-at-the-local-Zila-school-ground-from-November-7-to-11-The-four-day-programme-being-organised-by-Vishwa-Dharma-Jagaran-Manch-is-expected-to-garner-huge-crowd-in-wake-of-the-popularity-that-Maharaj-has-gained-while-giving-similar-discourse-in-other-cities-of-the-country-/articleshow/6823669.cms |title=Jain Muni Pramansagar ji Maharaj disciple of Acharya Vidyasagar ji |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=27 October 2010 |access-date=12 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413075941/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Jain-Muni-Pramansagar-ji-Maharaj-disciple-of-Acharya-Vidyasagar-ji-Maharaj-would-discourse-on-Ramayana-and-Geeta-at-the-local-Zila-school-ground-from-November-7-to-11-The-four-day-programme-being-organised-by-Vishwa-Dharma-Jagaran-Manch-is-expected-to-garner-huge-crowd-in-wake-of-the-popularity-that-Maharaj-has-gained-while-giving-similar-discourse-in-other-cities-of-the-country-/articleshow/6823669.cms |archive-date=13 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> One of his best known disciples, Muni [[Kshamasagar]] ji, obtained ''samadhi'' in 2015.<ref>[\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923\u0940\u092d\u0935\u0928 \u092e\u094b\u0930\u093e\u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u094d\u0937\u092e\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0938\u092e\u093e\u0927\u093f\u092e\u0930\u0923, Patrika, 2015-03-13]</ref>\n\nAcharya Pushadantasagar, the guru of  [[Tarun Sagar]] was initiated as a ''[[kshullak]]'' (junior monk) by Acharya Vidyasagar, although he took ''muni [[diksha]]'' from Acharya [[Vimal Sagar]]. Upadhyaya [[Guptisagar]] took ''muni diksha'' in 1982 from Acharya Vidyasagar although he later joined the ''[[sangha]]'' (community) of Acharya Vidyanand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/the-invincible-ascetie-aacharya-shri-vidyasagar/|title=The Invincible Ascetic Aacharya Shri Vidyasagar|website=\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205003328/https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/the-invincible-ascetie-aacharya-shri-vidyasagar/|archive-date=5 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAcharya Vidyasagar has been a source of inspiration to the people for founding institutions for their welfare at different locations.{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}} Since the number of monks (''munis'') and nuns (''\u0101ryikas'') initiated and directed by him exceeds two hundred (117 Digambar Muni, 172 Aryikas), they stay in more than 60 locations in India during ''Chaturmas'', ranging from Gujarat to Jharkhand, and Haryana to Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/acharyashri/89-2/shishyagan-chaturmas-2009/ |title=\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u092f \u0917\u0923 \u2013 \u091a\u093e\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0938 2009 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426162029/http://www.vidyasagar.net/acharyashri/89-2/shishyagan-chaturmas-2009/ |archive-date=26 April 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This insures that only a few monks or nuns are staying in one place.\n\n==His wanderings (''Vihara'')==\n[[File:Maharajji_1.jpg|thumb|alt= Picture of Acharya Vidyasagar leading his ''sangha'' |Acharya Vidyasagar leading his ''sangha'' during his ''vihara'', passers-by kneel in reverence]]\n\nAs a traditional ''Digambara'' Jain monk, Acharya Vidyasagar never stays in a single location for more than a few days, except for the four months of the rainy season (''Chaturmas''). He never declares where he will be next, although people try to guess his next destination.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/latest-story-of-acharya-shri-vidyasagar-maharaj-in-jabalpur-1529939/ |title=\u0926\u092f\u094b\u0926\u092f \u0917\u094c\u0936\u093e\u0932\u093e \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940, \u0939\u094b\u0932\u0940 \u092a\u0930 \u0926\u093f\u092f\u093e \u092f\u0939 \u0938\u0902\u0926\u0947\u0936, Patrika, 3/13/2017 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327182031/http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/latest-story-of-acharya-shri-vidyasagar-maharaj-in-jabalpur-1529939/ |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-VID-MAT-latest-vidisha-news-053003-559509-NOR.html |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u0938\u0902\u0918 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0935\u0947\u0936 \u0906\u091c, Bhaskar News Network, Jul 15, 2016 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327171300/http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-VID-MAT-latest-vidisha-news-053003-559509-NOR.html |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Since his initiation in 1968 he has had: seven ''Chaturmas'' in Rajasthan (1968\u201374), one in Uttar Pradesh (1974), seven in Madhya Pradesh (1976\u20131982), one in Bihar (1983), nine in Madhya Pradesh again (1984\u20131992), two in Maharashtra (1993\u201394), one in Madhya Pradesh (1995), one in Gujarat (1996), 11 again in Madhya Pradesh (1997\u20132007), one again in Maharashtra (2008), eight again in Madhya Pradesh (2009\u20132016).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/acharya-shri-ji-ke-chaturmas/ |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u091c\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u093e\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0938, September 28, 2017 |access-date=14 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174320/https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/acharya-shri-ji-ke-chaturmas/ |archive-date=14 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe fiftieth anniversary of his ''diksha'' was celebrated in many cities in India with parades and festivities in July 2018.<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/vidyasagar-maharaj-showed-us-the-right-path-say-jain-devotees/articleshow/59360144.cms  Vidyasagar Maharaj showed us the right path, say Jain devotees, TNN Jun 29, 2017]</ref> On this occasion, commemorative columns (''Swarna Kirti Stambha'') were erected in Ajmer<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/ajmer/news/latest-ajmer-news-041003-2095046.html |title=\u0905\u091c\u092e\u0947\u0930 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e 71 \u092b\u0940\u091f \u090a\u0902\u091a\u093e \u0915\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0924\u093f \u0938\u094d\u0924\u0902\u092d,  Danik Bhaskar, Jul 01, 2018 |access-date=25 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926014311/https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/ajmer/news/latest-ajmer-news-041003-2095046.html |archive-date=26 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=APfoLpMUZrg  \u0938\u0902\u092f\u092e \u0938\u094d\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0915\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0924\u093f \u0938\u094d\u0924\u092e\u094d\u092d : Amazing Architecture : Jain Temple In Ajmer, Rajasthan India,  Jun 28, 2018]</ref>, Rewa,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.patrika.com/rewa-news/jain-samaj-founded-21-feet-high-sanyam-kirti-stambh-in-rewa-2121229/ |title=Jain Samaj Founded 21 feet high sanyam kirti stambh in Rewa |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925025518/https://www.patrika.com/rewa-news/jain-samaj-founded-21-feet-high-sanyam-kirti-stambh-in-rewa-2121229/ |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Sravanbelgola and other locations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/kishangarh/news/latest-kishangarh-news-045503-2172013.html |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0902\u092f\u092e \u0938\u094d\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u091c\u092f\u0902\u0924\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928 \u092a\u0930 \u0915\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e 13 \u0938\u0947, Danik Bhaskar {{!}} Jul 12, 2018 |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925031147/https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/kishangarh/news/latest-kishangarh-news-045503-2172013.html |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nHis disciple ''Muni'' [[Kshamasagar]] wrote his biography ''\u0100tm\u0101nve\u015bh\u012b'' (hi:\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928\u094d\u0935\u0947\u0937\u0940) which was translated into English as ''In Quest of the Self'' and was published by [[Bhartiya Jnanpith]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=4}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nA documentary titled ''Vidyoday'' was released on 25 November 2018 by [[Landmarc Films|Landmark Films]].<ref>{{Citation|last=LandmarcFilms|title=Vidyoday {{!}} Acharya Vidyasagar {{!}} Teaser 04 {{!}} Documentary {{!}} Landmarc Films|date=22 September 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V9XhyY2ei50|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref> A trailer was also released. The film is directed by [[Vidhi Kasliwal]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Vidyoday|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9044540/|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref> ''Vidyoday'' had its first international screening at <!--[http://www.safaricinema.com/showTimings.html---> the Harrow Safari Cinema in [[London]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrZ0Flihf7k/|title=Vidhi Kasliwal on Instagram: \"LONDON calling! So excited about our first international screening!! Looking forward to the feedback!! #Vidyoday #AcharyaVidyasagar\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Jain Philosophy]]\n* [[List of Jains]]\n* [[Ahimsa in Jainism]]\n\n== References ==\n=== Notes ===\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation |last=Fl\u00fcgel |first=Peter |authorlink=Peter Fl\u00fcgel |title=Studies in Jaina History and Culture: Disputes and Dialogues |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U2cDn8bNbXAC |date=2006 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |isbn=978-0-203-00853-9 }}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Gita |title=Acharya Vidyasagar |date=1978 |ref={{sfnref|Gita Jain|1978}} }}\n*{{citation |author=Kshamasagar |authorlink=Kshamasagar |title=In Quest of Self : The life story of Acharya Shri Vidyasagar |publisher=[[Bhartiya Jnanpith]] |date=2007 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MSieVNwsAAIC |location= Delhi |isbn=81-263-1166-5 }}\n*{{citation |last=Shah |first=Natubhai |authorlink=Natubhai Shah |title=Jainism: The World of Conquerors |publisher=[[Sussex Academy Press]] |date=1998 |location=[[Sussex]] |volume=I and II |isbn=1-898723-30-3 |ref={{sfnref|Natubhai Shah|1998}} }}\n* {{citation|last=Vidyasagar|first=Acharya|title=The Silent Earth [M\u016bkam\u0101\u1e6d\u012b]|year=2010|publisher=[[Bharatiya Jnanpith]] |location=New Delhi|isbn=978-81-263-1875-9|editor=Lal Chandra Jain|series=Moortidevi Granthamala: English Series No. 22}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n*{{citation|last1=M\u0101cave|first1=Prabh\u0101kara|last2=R\u0101mam\u016brti|first2=Trip\u0101\u1e6dh\u012b|title=M\u016bkam\u0101\u1e6d\u012b-M\u012bm\u0101\u1e43s\u0101|volume=1, 2 & 3|publisher=Bhartiya Jnanpith|language=Hindi}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Vidyasagar (Jain monk)}}\n* {{Official website|https://vidyasagar.guru}}\n* [https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.app.vidyasagar&hl=en Official android app]\n{{Jain Gurus}}\n{{Jainism topics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vidyasagar, Acharya}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Belgaum district]]\n[[Category:Scholars from Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Digambara Acharyas]]\n[[Category:Jain writers]]\n[[Category:Indian Jain monks]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian Jains]]\n[[Category:20th-century Jain monks]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian monks]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian Jains]]\n[[Category:21st-century Jain monks]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian monks]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox religious biography\n| honorific-prefix = ''Sant Shiromani Acharya Shri'' 108\n| name = Vidyasagar\n| honorific-suffix = ''Ji Maharaj''\n| image = Acharya5 (cropped).jpg\n| alt = VIDHYADHAR\n| caption = Acharya Vidyasagar, a prominent ''[[Digambara monk]]''\n| religion = [[Jainism]]\n| sect = ''[[Digambara]]''\n| birth_name = Vidyadhar\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|10|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sadalga]], [[Belgaum district]], [[Karnataka]]\n| father = Mallappa (name after diksha-Mallinath ji)\n| mother = Shrimanti(name after diksha-Samaymati Ji)\n| initiation_date = 30 June 1968\n| initiation_place = [[Ajmer]]\n| initiator = ''Acharya'' [[Gyansagar]]\n| predecessor = ''muni\"[[Gyansagar]]\n| disciples = [[Pramansagar]], [[Sudhasagar]], [[Kshamasagar]], [[Guptisagar]]\n| works = ''Mukamati'' (silent soil)\n| website = {{URL|https://vidyasagar.guru}}\n}}\n{{Jainism}}\n'''Acharya Shri Vidyasagarji Maharaj''' (born 10 October 1946) is one of the best-known modern ''[[Digambara]]'' Jain ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' (Digambar Jain Monk). He is recognized both for his scholarship and ''[[tapasya]]'' (austerity). He is known for his long hours in meditation. While he was born in Karnataka and took ''[[diksha]]'' (undertook spiritual discipline) in [[Rajasthan]], he generally spends much of his time in the [[Bundelkhand]] region where he is credited with having brought about a revival in educational and religious activities.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/religion/story/20021125-aggressive-movement-to-revive-jainism-sweeps-central-india-794269-2002-11-25 |title=Aggressive movement to revive Jainism sweeps central India |first=Neeraj |last=Mishra |work=[[India Today]] |date=25 November 2002 |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925025751/https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/religion/story/20021125-aggressive-movement-to-revive-jainism-sweeps-central-india-794269-2002-11-25 |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He has written [[Haiku]] poems and the epic Hindi poem \"Mukamati\". His life is the subject of the 2018 documentary film ''Vidyoday'' released by [[Landmarc Films|Landmark Films]].\n\n==Life==\n===Early Life===\n\nVidyasagar was born on 10 October 1946 during the full moon festival (''[[Sharad Purnima]]''} in [[Sadalga]], in the [[Belgaum district]], of [[Karnataka]]. \n\nHis childhood name was Vidyadhar.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=23, 35}} He was the second of four sons, the eldest son being Mahavira Ashtage.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=34-35}} As a child, he was fond of eating fresh butter which was used to make [[ghee]] (clarified butter).{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=37}} He was not a demanding child and accepted what was given to him.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=40}} Vidyadhar used to visit temples and teach his younger siblings the principles of religion.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=41-42}} He called both younger sisters ''\"Akka\"'' (elder sister). He was attentive and was eager to undertake his studies. In his spare time he used to paint.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=42}}\n\n===Initiation===\nHe was initiated as a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' in 1968 at the age of 22 by Acharya [[Gyansagar]], who belonged to the lineage of Acharya [[Shantisagar]], at [[Ajmer]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=28}} His father Mallappa, his mother Shrimati, and two sisters took ''diksha'' and joined the ''[[sangha (Jainism)|sangha]]'' (community of the pious) of Acharya Dharmasagar.{{sfn|Gita Jain|1978|pp=8-14}} Except for his eldest brother, his remaining brothers, Anantanath and Shantinath, followed him and were initiated by Acharya Vidyasagar as Muni Yogasagar and Muni Samaysagar respectively.{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=73}} His elder brother married and continued the blood line.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/when-acharya-vidyasagar-had-secretly-listen-to-vinoba-bhave-1317790 |title=\u091c\u092c \u091b\u093f\u092a\u0915\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0928\u094b\u092c\u093e \u092d\u093e\u0935\u0947 \u0915\u094b \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0928\u0947 \u0917\u090f \u0925\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 |work=Patrika |date=8 June 2016 |access-date=18 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514142120/https://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/when-acharya-vidyasagar-had-secretly-listen-to-vinoba-bhave-1317790/ |archive-date=14 May 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe was elevated to the ''Acharya'' status in 1972.{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}} An Acharya does not eat salt, sugar, fruits, milk, in addition to what is traditionally prohibited (like onions). He goes out for a meal at about 9:30&nbsp;a.m.\u201310:00&nbsp;a.m. from ''[[\u015ar\u0101vaka (Jainism)|\u015ar\u0101vakas]]'' (lay votaries). He takes food once a day in the palm of his hand, one morsel at a time.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/damoh/amazing-rules-and-rituals-of-acharya-shri-vidhyasagar-ki-aharchariya-1315343/ |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0906\u0939\u093e\u0930\u091a\u0930\u094d\u092f\u093e \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0938\u091c\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u091a\u094c\u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0902, \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u093f\u0928 \u091a\u0940\u091c\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u0947\u0916 \u091b\u094b\u0921\u093c \u0926\u0947\u0924\u0947 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0916\u093e\u0928\u093e, Patrika, 2016-06-05 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327235123/http://www.patrika.com/news/damoh/amazing-rules-and-rituals-of-acharya-shri-vidhyasagar-ki-aharchariya-1315343/ |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn 1999, then Prime Minister [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]] paid a visit to Acharya Ji during his visit to <!--[http://www.indorerocks.com/attractions/attraction/Gomatgiri/10028---> Gomatgiri Indore.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/shri-atal-bihari-vaypayee-ji-had-visited-acharyashree-in-gomtagiri-indore/|title=Video : \u0938\u0928\u094d 1999 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0905\u091f\u0932 \u092c\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093e\u092f\u092a\u0947\u092f\u0940 \u091c\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u0917\u094b\u092e\u094d\u092e\u091f\u0917\u093f\u0930\u093f \u0907\u0902\u0926\u094c\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u0915\u093f\u090f \u0925\u0947|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503090356/http://www.vidyasagar.net/shri-atal-bihari-vaypayee-ji-had-visited-acharyashree-in-gomtagiri-indore/|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Jain_inscription_Vidyasagar.jpg|thumb|alt= Photograph showing the inscription oin a Parshvanath idol | Inscription on a Parshvanath idol at Orchha mentioning the lineage of Acharya Vidyasagar from Acharya Shantisagar. He is termed ''anasakta yogi'', ''jyeshtha'', ''shreshtha'', ''sant shiromani'']]\n\nAcharya Vidyasagar's ''[[Chaturmas]]'' (four month stay) in 2016 was in [[Bhopal]], [[Madhya Pradesh]],<ref>{{citation |url=http://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-acharya-vidyasagar-thief-arrested-four-female-chef-program-seized-seven-gold-chain-786987 |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u093e\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093f\u0932\u093e \u091a\u094b\u0930 \u0917\u093f\u0930\u092b\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0930, \u0938\u093e\u0924 \u0938\u094b\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u091a\u0948\u0928 \u091c\u092a\u094d\u0924 |work=[[Nai Duniya]] |date=27 July 2016 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728165237/http://naidunia.jagran.com/madhya-pradesh/bhopal-acharya-vidyasagar-thief-arrested-four-female-chef-program-seized-seven-gold-chain-786987 |archive-date=28 July 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> where he was accompanied by 38 ''munis''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3kd0xm2NMXhUFc5YnZydWVyNFk/view |title=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Sangh Parichaya book 2016.pdf |access-date=28 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413235707/https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3kd0xm2NMXhUFc5YnZydWVyNFk/view |archive-date=13 April 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He gave his ''[[Pravachana]]'' (reading) in the [[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly]] by special invitation from [[Chief Minister of Madhya Pradesh|Chief Minister]] [[Shivraj Singh Chouhan]] on 28 July 2016.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/bhopal/jain-saint-vidya-sagar-to-give-spiritual-speech-in-mp-assembly-1360946 |title=\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u0947 \u0907\u0924\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0928\u093e\u090f \u0930\u0916\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u092a\u0915\u094d\u0937-\u0935\u093f\u092a\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u0938\u093e\u0925 \u0915\u093e\u092e \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902: \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 |work=[[Rajasthan Patrika]] |date=28 July 2016 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803205001/http://www.patrika.com/news/bhopal/jain-saint-vidya-sagar-to-give-spiritual-speech-in-mp-assembly-1360946/ |archive-date=3 August 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/08/29/when-another-jain-monk-addressed-a-state-legislative-assembly-an |title=When Another Jain Monk Addressed A State Legislative Assembly And There Was No Controversy |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=29 August 2016 |access-date=31 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160830162242/http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/08/29/when-another-jain-monk-addressed-a-state-legislative-assembly-an/ |archive-date=30 August 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2016, during a trip to Bhopal, Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] visited him.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/why-is-modi-keen-to-meet-acharya-vidyasagar/story-3ZbjQ5aVjnSy3NfrVQhUdK.html |title=Why is Modi keen to meet Acharya Vidyasagar? |last=Ranjan |location=[[Bhopal]] |date=14 October 2016 |access-date=17 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017172340/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/why-is-modi-keen-to-meet-acharya-vidyasagar/story-3ZbjQ5aVjnSy3NfrVQhUdK.html |archive-date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was also visited by former Union minister [[Jyotiraditya 