6|work=www.patrika.com|language=hindi|access-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503105256/https://www.patrika.com/chhatarpur-news/digvijay-singh-blesses-acharya-vidyasagarji-gurupurnima-3170044/|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2018, American ambassador [[Kenneth Juster]] paid a visit to Acharya Vidyasagar Ji and assured him he would follow a full [[Vegetarianism|vegetarian]] diet for one day a week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/bhopal/news/american-ambassador-junkie-influenced-by-acharya-vidyasagar-5926529.html|title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0938\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u092d\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u0941\u090f \u0905\u092e\u0947\u0930\u093f\u0915\u0940 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u0926\u0942\u0924 \u091c\u0938\u094d\u091f\u0930; \u0915\u0939\u093e- \u0939\u092b\u094d\u0924\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u090f\u0915 \u0926\u093f\u0928 \u0930\u0939\u0942\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0936\u093e\u0915\u093e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u0940|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=2018-12-03|language=hi|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005700/https://www.bhaskar.com/mp/bhopal/news/american-ambassador-junkie-influenced-by-acharya-vidyasagar-5926529.html|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> French Diplomat [[Alexandre Ziegler]] visited [[Khajuraho Group of Monuments|Khajuraho]] with his family in 2018 and felt \"peaceful and blessed\" after meeting Acharya Vidyasagar Ji. He vowed to become a vegetarian.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/french-diplomat-vows-to-turn-veggie-after-meeting-jain-muni/articleshow/66397413.cms|title=French diplomat vows to turn vegetarian after meeting Jain muni - Times of India|work=[[The Times of India]]|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref>\n\n[[Uttar Pradesh]] Chief Minister [[Yogi Adityanath]] has declared the State Guest Honor to Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj. In this regard, the UP Government also issued a protocol.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.patrika.com/lalitpur-news/acharya-vidyasagar-ji-will-be-honoured-with-rajkiya-atithi-samman-3727424/|title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u094b \u0930\u093e\u091c\u0915\u0940\u092f \u0905\u0924\u093f\u0925\u093f \u0938\u092e\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928, \u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0918\u094b\u0937\u0923\u093e|work=www.patrika.com|access-date=2018-11-27|language=hi-IN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181126004003/https://www.patrika.com/lalitpur-news/acharya-vidyasagar-ji-will-be-honoured-with-rajkiya-atithi-samman-3727424/|archive-date=26 November 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nUnion Home Minister Shri [[Rajnath Singh|Rajnath Singh Ji]] has taken the blessings of Acharya Vidyasagar Ji in [[Jabalpur]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/rajnathsingh/status/1119921007605760000|title=\u092e\u0927\u094d\u092f \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u0941\u0928\u093e\u0935\u0940 \u0926\u094c\u0930\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0935\u094d\u092f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0924\u093e\u0913\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u092c\u0940\u091a \u092e\u0941\u091d\u0947 \u0906\u091c \u091c\u0948\u0928 \u092e\u0941\u0928\u093f, \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930\u091c\u0940  \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u094c\u092d\u093e\u0917\u094d\u092f \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e\u0964 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u0930\u0923\u094b\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094b\u091f\u093f\u0936: \u0928\u092e\u0928!pic.twitter.com/j4c5wPTn4N|last=Singh|first=Chowkidar Rajnath|date=2019-04-21|website=@rajnathsingh|language=hi|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n* Acharya Vidyasagara is a scholar of [[Sanskrit]] and [[Prakrit]] and knows several languages including [[Hindi]] and [[Kannada]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=26}} He has written in languages such as Prakrit, Sanskrit, Hindi. His works include ''Niranjana Shataka'', ''Bhavana Shataka'', ''Parishah Jaya Shataka'', ''Suniti Shataka'' and ''Shramana Shataka''.<ref>Ek Tapahput kavi ki kavya Sadhna, Asha Malaiya, Tirthankar, Nov-Dec 78, p. 21-24</ref> \n* He has composed nearly 700 [[haiku]] poems which are unpublished.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.pinterest.com/vidyasagar_guru/haiku-poems-by-acharya-vidyasagar-ji/|title=Haiku Poems by Acharya Vidyasagar Ji|website=Pinterest|language=en|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/haiku-17265/|title=\u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|access-date=2018-11-02|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807091030/http://www.vidyasagar.net/haiku-17265/|archive-date=7 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vidyasagar.guru/haiku/|title=\u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942 \u0938\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0927\u094d\u092f\u093e\u092f - \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u0939\u093e\u092f\u0915\u0942 \u0914\u0930 \u0906\u092a\u0915\u0940 \u0938\u092e\u091d - \u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|website=\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005632/https://vidyasagar.guru/haiku/|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* He wrote the Hindi epic poem \"Mukamati\".{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}}<ref name=\"webindia2\" /> This has been included in the syllabus of Hindi MA programmes at various institutions.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MPc-58-1943771-NOR.html |title=\u092c\u0940\u092f\u0942 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u093f\u0932\u0947\u092c\u0938 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091c\u0948\u0928 \u0917\u094d\u0930\u0902\u0925 '\u092e\u0942\u0915\u092e\u093e\u091f\u0940' \u0915\u094b \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=24 May 2013 |access-date=31 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308234934/http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MPc-58-1943771-NOR.html |archive-date=8 March 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This has been translated into English by <!--[https://www.jainworld.com/society/speaksch/dalchand.htm---> Lal Chandra Jain and was presented to the [[President of India]].<ref name=\"webindia2\" /><ref name=\"jainworld.com\">{{citation|url=http://jainworld.com/GJE.asp?id=54|title=Acharya Vidyasagar's Book \"Silent Earth\" Presented To President|work=jainworld.com|access-date=10 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316143001/http://jainworld.com/GJE.asp?id=54|archive-date=16 March 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>{{sfn|Vidyasagar|2010|p=}} Several researchers have studied his works for masters and doctoral degrees.<ref name=\"webindia2\">{{citation |url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20110615/1772295.html |title=Acharya Vidyasagar's book \"Silent Earth\" presented to President |work=[[Web India 123]] |date=15 June 2011 |access-date=12 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163303/http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20110615/1772295.html |archive-date=14 July 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n<!--<blockquote>\u0926\u094b \u0939\u093f\u0924 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0928\u093f\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u094b\u0902, \u0935\u0939 '\u0926\u0941\u0939\u093f\u0924\u093e' \u0915\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948<br />\u0905\u092a\u0928\u093e \u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u094d\u0935\u092f\u0902 \u0939\u0940 \u0915\u0930 \u0932\u0947\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948, \u092a\u0924\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u0947 \u092a\u0924\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093e \u091c\u0940\u0935\u0928 \u092d\u0940<br />\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0938\u0947 \u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924 \u0939\u094b\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0938\u0947 \u0935\u0939 '\u0926\u0941\u0939\u093f\u0924\u093e' \u0915\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964 <br />\u0906\u0908\u092f\u0947\u2026\u0910\u0938\u0940 \u092c\u0947\u091f\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u093e\u0925 \u092e\u093f\u0932\u0915\u0930 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u2026<br />\u090f\u0915 \u0913\u0930\u2026'\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928'   An excerpt from ''Mukamati (\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928)''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/betiyan/|title=\u092c\u0947\u091f\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0901|work=Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj {{!}} Vidyasagar Ji Maharaj Pravachan {{!}} Jain Religion In Hindi|access-date=2018-12-04|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205004740/http://www.vidyasagar.net/betiyan/|archive-date=5 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref></blockquote>  This should be translated into English if it is to be included in the article.--->\n\n==His tradition==\nAcharya Vidyasagar belongs to the tradition established by Acharya [[Shantisagar]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=51}} Acharya Shantisagar initiated Acharya Virasagar, who was then succeeded by Acharya Shivsagar, Acharya [[Gyansagar]]<ref>{{citation |title=\u0907\u0938 \u0938\u0902\u0924 \u0915\u0947 \u091c\u0940\u0935\u0924 \u0930\u0939\u0924\u0947 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0942\u0921\u0947\u0902\u091f \u0915\u0930 \u0930\u0939\u0947 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0907\u0928 \u092a\u0930 PHD, \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094d\u092f\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0907\u0928\u0915\u0940 \u0916\u0942\u092c\u0940 |url=http://m.bhaskar.com/news/c-58-3193036-bp0851-NOR.html |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=17 October 2016 |access-date=28 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028215045/http://m.bhaskar.com/news/c-58-3193036-bp0851-NOR.html |archive-date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>and finally Acharya Vidyasagar.\n\nSome of his disciples are well-known scholars in their own right. {{As of|2001}}, about 21% of all the ''Digambar'' monks were under Acharya Vidyasagara.{{sfn|Fl\u00fcgel|2006|p=356}} Muni [[Sudhasagar]] and Muni [[Pramansagar]] are also his disciples.<ref>{{citation |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Jain-Muni-Pramansagar-ji-Maharaj-disciple-of-Acharya-Vidyasagar-ji-Maharaj-would-discourse-on-Ramayana-and-Geeta-at-the-local-Zila-school-ground-from-November-7-to-11-The-four-day-programme-being-organised-by-Vishwa-Dharma-Jagaran-Manch-is-expected-to-garner-huge-crowd-in-wake-of-the-popularity-that-Maharaj-has-gained-while-giving-similar-discourse-in-other-cities-of-the-country-/articleshow/6823669.cms |title=Jain Muni Pramansagar ji Maharaj disciple of Acharya Vidyasagar ji |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=27 October 2010 |access-date=12 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413075941/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Jain-Muni-Pramansagar-ji-Maharaj-disciple-of-Acharya-Vidyasagar-ji-Maharaj-would-discourse-on-Ramayana-and-Geeta-at-the-local-Zila-school-ground-from-November-7-to-11-The-four-day-programme-being-organised-by-Vishwa-Dharma-Jagaran-Manch-is-expected-to-garner-huge-crowd-in-wake-of-the-popularity-that-Maharaj-has-gained-while-giving-similar-discourse-in-other-cities-of-the-country-/articleshow/6823669.cms |archive-date=13 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> One of his best known disciples, Muni [[Kshamasagar]] ji, obtained ''samadhi'' in 2015.<ref>[\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923\u0940\u092d\u0935\u0928 \u092e\u094b\u0930\u093e\u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u094d\u0937\u092e\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0938\u092e\u093e\u0927\u093f\u092e\u0930\u0923, Patrika, 2015-03-13]</ref>\n\nAcharya Pushadantasagar, the guru of  [[Tarun Sagar]] was initiated as a ''[[kshullak]]'' (junior monk) by Acharya Vidyasagar, although he took ''muni [[diksha]]'' from Acharya [[Vimal Sagar]]. Upadhyaya [[Guptisagar]] took ''muni diksha'' in 1982 from Acharya Vidyasagar although he later joined the ''[[sangha]]'' (community) of Acharya Vidyanand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/the-invincible-ascetie-aacharya-shri-vidyasagar/|title=The Invincible Ascetic Aacharya Shri Vidyasagar|website=\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0947 \u0917\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0935\u0930... \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0930\u093e\u091c|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205003328/https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/the-invincible-ascetie-aacharya-shri-vidyasagar/|archive-date=5 December 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAcharya Vidyasagar has been a source of inspiration to the people for founding institutions for their welfare at different locations.{{sfn|Natubhai Shah|1998|pp=56\u201357}} Since the number of monks (''munis'') and nuns (''\u0101ryikas'') initiated and directed by him exceeds two hundred (117 Digambar Muni, 172 Aryikas), they stay in more than 60 locations in India during ''Chaturmas'', ranging from Gujarat to Jharkhand, and Haryana to Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vidyasagar.net/acharyashri/89-2/shishyagan-chaturmas-2009/ |title=\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u092f \u0917\u0923 \u2013 \u091a\u093e\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0938 2009 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426162029/http://www.vidyasagar.net/acharyashri/89-2/shishyagan-chaturmas-2009/ |archive-date=26 April 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This insures that only a few monks or nuns are staying in one place.\n\n==His wanderings (''Vihara'')==\n[[File:Maharajji_1.jpg|thumb|alt= Picture of Acharya Vidyasagar leading his ''sangha'' |Acharya Vidyasagar leading his ''sangha'' during his ''vihara'', passers-by kneel in reverence]]\n\nAs a traditional ''Digambara'' Jain monk, Acharya Vidyasagar never stays in a single location for more than a few days, except for the four months of the rainy season (''Chaturmas''). He never declares where he will be next, although people try to guess his next destination.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/latest-story-of-acharya-shri-vidyasagar-maharaj-in-jabalpur-1529939/ |title=\u0926\u092f\u094b\u0926\u092f \u0917\u094c\u0936\u093e\u0932\u093e \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0947 \u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940, \u0939\u094b\u0932\u0940 \u092a\u0930 \u0926\u093f\u092f\u093e \u092f\u0939 \u0938\u0902\u0926\u0947\u0936, Patrika, 3/13/2017 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327182031/http://www.patrika.com/news/jabalpur/latest-story-of-acharya-shri-vidyasagar-maharaj-in-jabalpur-1529939/ |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-VID-MAT-latest-vidisha-news-053003-559509-NOR.html |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u091c\u0940 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u0938\u0902\u0918 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0935\u0947\u0936 \u0906\u091c, Bhaskar News Network, Jul 15, 2016 |access-date=27 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327171300/http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-VID-MAT-latest-vidisha-news-053003-559509-NOR.html |archive-date=27 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Since his initiation in 1968 he has had: seven ''Chaturmas'' in Rajasthan (1968\u201374), one in Uttar Pradesh (1974), seven in Madhya Pradesh (1976\u20131982), one in Bihar (1983), nine in Madhya Pradesh again (1984\u20131992), two in Maharashtra (1993\u201394), one in Madhya Pradesh (1995), one in Gujarat (1996), 11 again in Madhya Pradesh (1997\u20132007), one again in Maharashtra (2008), eight again in Madhya Pradesh (2009\u20132016).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/acharya-shri-ji-ke-chaturmas/ |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u091c\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u091a\u093e\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0938, September 28, 2017 |access-date=14 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174320/https://vidyasagar.guru/articles.html/jeewan-parichay/acharya-shri-ji-ke-chaturmas/ |archive-date=14 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe fiftieth anniversary of his ''diksha'' was celebrated in many cities in India with parades and festivities in July 2018.<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/vidyasagar-maharaj-showed-us-the-right-path-say-jain-devotees/articleshow/59360144.cms  Vidyasagar Maharaj showed us the right path, say Jain devotees, TNN Jun 29, 2017]</ref> On this occasion, commemorative columns (''Swarna Kirti Stambha'') were erected in Ajmer<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/ajmer/news/latest-ajmer-news-041003-2095046.html |title=\u0905\u091c\u092e\u0947\u0930 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e 71 \u092b\u0940\u091f \u090a\u0902\u091a\u093e \u0915\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0924\u093f \u0938\u094d\u0924\u0902\u092d,  Danik Bhaskar, Jul 01, 2018 |access-date=25 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926014311/https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/ajmer/news/latest-ajmer-news-041003-2095046.html |archive-date=26 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=APfoLpMUZrg  \u0938\u0902\u092f\u092e \u0938\u094d\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0915\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0924\u093f \u0938\u094d\u0924\u092e\u094d\u092d : Amazing Architecture : Jain Temple In Ajmer, Rajasthan India,  Jun 28, 2018]</ref>, Rewa,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.patrika.com/rewa-news/jain-samaj-founded-21-feet-high-sanyam-kirti-stambh-in-rewa-2121229/ |title=Jain Samaj Founded 21 feet high sanyam kirti stambh in Rewa |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925025518/https://www.patrika.com/rewa-news/jain-samaj-founded-21-feet-high-sanyam-kirti-stambh-in-rewa-2121229/ |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Sravanbelgola and other locations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/kishangarh/news/latest-kishangarh-news-045503-2172013.html |title=\u0906\u091a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u093e\u0917\u0930 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0902\u092f\u092e \u0938\u094d\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u091c\u092f\u0902\u0924\u0940 \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928 \u092a\u0930 \u0915\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e 13 \u0938\u0947, Danik Bhaskar {{!}} Jul 12, 2018 |access-date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925031147/https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/kishangarh/news/latest-kishangarh-news-045503-2172013.html |archive-date=25 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nHis disciple ''Muni'' [[Kshamasagar]] wrote his biography ''\u0100tm\u0101nve\u015bh\u012b'' (hi:\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928\u094d\u0935\u0947\u0937\u0940) which was translated into English as ''In Quest of the Self'' and was published by [[Bhartiya Jnanpith]].{{sfn|Kshamasagar|2007|p=4}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nA documentary titled ''Vidyoday'' was released on 25 November 2018 by [[Landmarc Films|Landmark Films]].<ref>{{Citation|last=LandmarcFilms|title=Vidyoday {{!}} Acharya Vidyasagar {{!}} Teaser 04 {{!}} Documentary {{!}} Landmarc Films|date=22 September 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V9XhyY2ei50|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref> A trailer was also released. The film is directed by [[Vidhi Kasliwal]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Vidyoday|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9044540/|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref> ''Vidyoday'' had its first international screening at <!--[http://www.safaricinema.com/showTimings.html---> the Harrow Safari Cinema in [[London]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrZ0Flihf7k/|title=Vidhi Kasliwal on Instagram: \"LONDON calling! So excited about our first international screening!! Looking forward to the feedback!! #Vidyoday #AcharyaVidyasagar\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Jain Philosophy]]\n* [[List of Jains]]\n* [[Ahimsa in Jainism]]\n\n== References ==\n=== Notes ===\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation |last=Fl\u00fcgel |first=Peter |authorlink=Peter Fl\u00fcgel |title=Studies in Jaina History and Culture: Disputes and Dialogues |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U2cDn8bNbXAC |date=2006 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |isbn=978-0-203-00853-9 }}\n* {{citation |last=Jain |first=Gita |title=Acharya Vidyasagar |date=1978 |ref={{sfnref|Gita Jain|1978}} }}\n*{{citation |author=Kshamasagar |authorlink=Kshamasagar |title=In Quest of Self : The life story of Acharya Shri Vidyasagar |publisher=[[Bhartiya Jnanpith]] |date=2007 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MSieVNwsAAIC |location= Delhi |isbn=81-263-1166-5 }}\n*{{citation |last=Shah |first=Natubhai |authorlink=Natubhai Shah |title=Jainism: The World of Conquerors |publisher=[[Sussex Academy Press]] |date=1998 |location=[[Sussex]] |volume=I and II |isbn=1-898723-30-3 |ref={{sfnref|Natubhai Shah|1998}} }}\n* {{citation|last=Vidyasagar|first